translations.description: بعد أن تأثر بالقرصان ذو الشعر الأحمر شانكس الذي يرتدي قبعة قش، يتبع الفتى المتحمس مونكي دي. لوفي أحلامه في أن يصبح ملك القراصنة ذات يوم
translations.title: فجر الرومانسية، فجر  المغامرة

translations.description: Beeinflusst von dem strohhuttragenden Piraten Rothaar Shanks, träumt ein begeisterter Junge namens Monkey D. Luffy davon, eines Tages König der Piraten zu werden.
translations.title: Romance Dawn - Der Anfang eines Abenteuers

translations.description: Influenced by the straw-hat-wearing pirate Red-Haired Shanks, an enthusiastic young boy named Monkey D. Luffy dreams of one day becoming king of the pirates.
translations.title: Romance Dawn, the Dawn of an Adventure

translations.description: Influenciado por un pirata llamado Shanks el Pelirrojo que porta un sombrero de paja, un entusiasta niño llamado Monkey D. Luffy sueña con algún día convertirse en el Rey de los Piratas.
translations.title: El amanecer de la aventura

translations.description: Influencé par le pirate Shanks le Roux, porteur d'un chapeau de paille, un jeune garçon enthousiaste nommé Monkey D. Luffy rêve de devenir un jour, le Roi des Pirates.
translations.title: L'Aube d'une Grande Aventure

translations.description: Influenced by the straw-hat-wearing pirate Red-Haired Shanks, an enthusiastic young boy named Monkey D. Luffy dreams of one day becoming king of the pirates.
translations.title: ROMANCE DAWN - 冒険の夜明け

translations.description: بينما ألفيدا وقراصنتها ينهبون سفينة رحلات، يجدون برميل يحتوي داخله فتى يدعى مونكي دي.لوفي، يصادق الجبان كوبي لوفي ويتحدثون عن أحلامهما فيما بينهما
translations.title: يسمونه لوفي المشهور بـ (قبعة القش)

translations.description: Während Alvida und ihre Piraten ein Kreuzfahrtschiff plündern, stoßen sie auf ein Fass mit einem seltsamen Jungen namens Monkey D. Luffy.  Der schüchterne Koby freundet sich mit Luffy an, und sie teilen ihre großen Träume miteinander.
translations.title: Hier kommt "Strohhut" Luffy!

translations.description: While Alvida and her pirates plunder a cruise ship, they come across a barrel containing a strange boy named Monkey D. Luffy. The timid Koby befriends Luffy, and they share their grand dreams with each other.
translations.title: They Call Him "Straw Hat" Luffy

translations.description: Mientras Alvida y sus piratas saquean un crucero, encuentran un barril que contenía un extraño muchacho llamado Monkey D. Luffy. El tímido Koby se hace amigo de este, y comparten sus sueños el uno con el otro.
translations.title: Luffy, el hombre del sombrero de paja

translations.description: Alors qu'Alvida et ses pirates pillent un bateau de croisière, ils tombent sur un tonneau contenant un étrange garçon nommé Monkey D. Luffy. Le timide Kobby se lie d'amitié avec Luffy, et ils partagent leurs grands rêves.
translations.title: On le surnomme "Chapeau de paille"

translations.description: While Alvida and her pirates plunder a cruise ship, they come across a barrel containing a strange boy named Monkey D. Luffy. The timid Koby befriends Luffy, and they share their grand dreams with each other.
translations.title: その男"麦わらのルフィ"

translations.description: باحثًا عن أعضاء لطاقم قراصنته، يصل لوفي بصحبه صديق الجديد كوبي إلى جزيرة بها مقر للبحرية، وهناك يبحثون عن صائد القراصنة الشهير زورو ولكنه يعترضهم هيليمبو، ابن العقيد الشهير مورغان
translations.title: ملك القراصنة والسياف الأعظم

translations.description: Auf der Suche nach Mitgliedern für seine Piratencrew gelangt Luffy mit seinem neuen Freund Koby auf eine Insel mit einer Marinefestung.  Dort spüren sie den berühmten Piratenjäger Zoro auf, geraten aber an Helmeppo, den Sohn des berüchtigten Kapitän Morgan.
translations.title: Piratenkönig und Meisterschwertkämpfer

translations.description: In search of members for his pirate crew, Luffy with his new friend Koby arrive at an island with a Navy stronghold. There, they track down the renowned Pirate Hunter Zoro but run afoul of Helmeppo, son of the infamous Captain Morgan.
translations.title: The Pirate King and the Master Swordsman

translations.description: Buscando miembros para su tripulación, Luffy, con su nuevo amigo, llegan a una isla controlada por la Marina. Pronto descubren que el famoso Cazador de Piratas Zoro, había sido arrestado por Helmeppo, el hijo del infame Capitán Morgan.
translations.title: Rey Pirata y Maestro Espadachín

translations.description: À la recherche de membres pour son équipage de pirates, Luffy et son nouvel ami Kobby arrivent sur une île avec un bastion de la Marine. Là, ils traquent le célèbre chasseur de pirates Zoro mais se heurtent à Hermep, fils du tristement célèbre capitaine Morgan.
translations.title: Le Roi des Pirates et le Grand Épéiste

translations.description: In search of members for his pirate crew, Luffy with his new friend Koby arrive at an island with a Navy stronghold. There, they track down the renowned Pirate Hunter Zoro but run afoul of Helmeppo, son of the infamous Captain Morgan.
translations.title: 海賊王と大剣豪

translations.description: يُقنع لوفي زورو بأن ينضم لطاقم قراصنته، ولكن عليهم أولًا هزيمة العقيد الطاغية مورغان
translations.title: الأول

translations.description: Luffy überredet den gefangenen Zoro, sich seiner Piratencrew anzuschließen, aber sie müssen erst den tyrannischen Kapitän Morgan besiegen.
translations.title: Nummer Eins

translations.description: Luffy convinces the captive Zoro to join his pirate crew, but they must first defeat the tyrannical Captain Morgan.
translations.title: The First

translations.description: Luffy convence al cautivo Zoro de que se una a su tripulación, pero primero deben derrotar al Capitán Morgan.
translations.title: El primer miembro

translations.description: Luffy convainc le captif Zoro de rejoindre son équipage de pirates, mais ils doivent d'abord vaincre le tyrannique capitaine Morgan.
translations.title: Le Premier

translations.description: Luffy convinces the captive Zoro to join his pirate crew, but they must first defeat the tyrannical Captain Morgan.
translations.title: 1人目

translations.description: ينطلق الفتى مونكي دي لوفي في مغامرة لتكوين طاقم من أجل العثور على كنز ون بيس الأسطوري ليصبح ملك القراصنة
translations.title: فجر الرومانسية

translations.description: Monkey D. Luffy sets out on an adventure to form a crew, find the legendary One Piece, and become the pirate king.

translations.description: Monkey D. Luffy sets out on an adventure to form a crew, find the legendary One Piece, and become the pirate king.
translations.title: Romance Dawn

translations.description: Monkey D. Luffy parte en su aventura para formar su tripulación, encontrar el legendario One Piece, y así, ser el Rey de los Piratas.
translations.title: Romance Dawn

translations.description: Monkey D. Luffy se lance dans une aventure pour former un équipage, trouver le légendaire One Piece et devenir le Roi des Pirates.
translations.title: Romance Dawn

translations.description: Monkey D. Luffy sets out on an adventure to form a crew, find the legendary One Piece, and become the pirate king.
translations.title: ROMANCE DAWN

translations.description: Nami, a street-smart girl who loves money and tangerines, makes Luffy's acquaintance. To save herself and steal a map to the Grand Line, she tricks Luffy into allowing her to turn him over to the infamous pirate Buggy the Clown.
translations.title: سارقة القراصنة نامي/القطة السارقة نامي

translations.description: Nami, a street-smart girl who loves money and tangerines, makes Luffy's acquaintance. To save herself and steal a map to the Grand Line, she tricks Luffy into allowing her to turn him over to the infamous pirate Buggy the Clown.
translations.title: Enter: Nami

translations.description: Nami, una inteligente chica que ama el dinero y las mandarinas, conoce a Luffy. Para salvarse de haber robado un mapa al Grand Line, engaña a Luffy para entregarlo al infame pirata, Buggy "el Payaso".
translations.title: Aparece Nami

translations.description: Nami, une fille intelligente qui aime l'argent et les mandarines, fait la connaissance de Luffy. Pour se sauver et voler une carte de Grand Line, elle trompe Luffy en le livrant au célèbre pirate, Baggy « Le Clown ».
translations.title: Nami

translations.description: Nami, a street-smart girl who loves money and tangerines, makes Luffy's acquaintance. To save herself and steal a map to the Grand Line, she tricks Luffy into allowing her to turn him over to the infamous pirate Buggy the Clown.
translations.title: 海賊専門泥棒ナミ

translations.description: Luffy meets a small dog guarding his late master’s store. Meanwhile, the beast tamer Mohji, the acrobat Cabaji, and the lion Richie show up in the streets of Orange Town to get revenge for Captain Buggy's humiliating loss.
translations.title: كنز تشوتشو

translations.description: Luffy meets a small dog guarding his late master’s store. Meanwhile, the beast tamer Mohji, the acrobat Cabaji, and the lion Richie show up in the streets of Orange Town to get revenge for Captain Buggy's humiliating loss.
translations.title: Treasure

translations.description: Luffy conoce a un pequeño perro que protege la tienda de su fallecido dueño. Mientras tanto, el domador de bestias Mohji, el acróbata Cabaji, y el león Richie aparecen en las calles de Orange Town para vengarse de la humillante derrota del Capitán Buggy.
translations.title: Tesoro

translations.description: Luffy rencontre un petit chien qui garde le magasin de son défunt maître. Pendant ce temps, le Dresseur de Fauves Morge, l'Acrobate Cabaji et le Lion Richy se présentent dans les rues du Village d'Orange pour venger la défaite humiliante du capitaine Baggy.
translations.title: Trésor

translations.description: Luffy meets a small dog guarding his late master’s store. Meanwhile, the beast tamer Mohji, the acrobat Cabaji, and the lion Richie show up in the streets of Orange Town to get revenge for Captain Buggy's humiliating loss.
translations.title: シュシュの宝

translations.description: Shockingly, it turns out Captain Buggy and Red-Haired Shanks share a common history. When the bombastic clown rips Shanks' straw hat, Luffy's rage knows no bounds.
translations.title: القرصان المهرج باغي

translations.description: Shockingly, it turns out Captain Buggy and Red-Haired Shanks share a common history. When the bombastic clown rips Shanks' straw hat, Luffy's rage knows no bounds.
translations.title: Pirate Buggy "the Clown"

translations.description: Sorpresivamente, resulta que Buggy y Shanks el Pelirrojo eran compañeros de tripulación. Cuando el ruidoso payaso rompe el sombrero de paja de Shanks, Luffy estalla de ira.
translations.title: Pirata Buggy "El Payaso"

translations.description: Surprenamment, il s'avère que le capitaine Baggy et Shanks le Roux partagent une histoire commune. Quand le clown déchire le chapeau de paille de Shanks, la rage de Luffy ne connaît aucune limite.
translations.title: Baggy le Clown

translations.description: Shockingly, it turns out Captain Buggy and Red-Haired Shanks share a common history. When the bombastic clown rips Shanks' straw hat, Luffy's rage knows no bounds.
translations.title: 海賊”道化のバギー”

translations.description: يعترض طريق لوفي وزورو طاقم قراصنة مبهرج يترأسهم قبطان يدعى المهرج باغي، تنضم لهم فتاة شابة اسمها نامي تساعدهم على الإبحار بعيدًا عن تلك المشكلة
translations.title: بلدة أورنج

translations.description: Luffy and Zoro run afoul of a flashy crew of pirates and their captain, Buggy the Clown. They are joined by a young girl named Nami who helps them navigate this predicament.
translations.title: Orange Town

translations.description: Luffy y Zoro se enfrentan a una colorida tripulación pirata liderada por el capitán Buggy, el Payaso. Se les une una muchacha llamada Nami, quien les ayuda a navegar en este predicamento.
translations.title: Ciudad Orange

translations.description: Luffy et Zoro se heurtent en grande pompe à un équipage de pirates et à leur capitaine, Baggy le Clown. Ils sont rejoints par une jeune fille nommée Nami qui va les aider à surmonter cette situation difficile.
translations.title: Village d'Orange

translations.description: Luffy and Zoro run afoul of a flashy crew of pirates and their captain, Buggy the Clown. They are joined by a young girl named Nami who helps them navigate this predicament.
translations.title: オレンジの町

translations.description: With Nami joining as Luffy's navigator (though not as an actual member of the crew), they arrive at an island in search of a proper ship. There they meet a man claiming to be a pirate captain who seemingly also has ties to Red-Haired Shanks.
translations.title: Captain Usopp

translations.description: With Nami joining as Luffy's navigator (though not as an actual member of the crew), they arrive at an island in search of a proper ship. There they meet a man claiming to be a pirate captain who seemingly also has ties to Red-Haired Shanks.
translations.title: キャプテン･ウソップ

translations.description: After uncovering a devious plot, Usopp warns the village and Kaya, but finds his years of lying make it difficult to convince people of the truth.
translations.title: Captain Kuro

translations.description: After uncovering a devious plot, Usopp warns the village and Kaya, but finds his years of lying make it difficult to convince people of the truth.
translations.title: キャプテン･クロ

translations.description: Usopp resolves that if he is to keep the peace, the town must continue to believe he is a liar, which means he cannot let Captain Kuro’s men up the slope to the village! Luffy, Zoro, and Nami aid Usopp in his plan to keep the Black Cat Pirates at bay.
translations.title: The Slope

translations.description: Usopp resolves that if he is to keep the peace, the town must continue to believe he is a liar, which means he cannot let Captain Kuro’s men up the slope to the village! Luffy, Zoro, and Nami aid Usopp in his plan to keep the Black Cat Pirates at bay.
translations.title: 坂道

translations.description: Captain Kuro makes his appearance, and with Zoro too injured to fight, Luffy incapacitated, and Usopp and Nami too weak to make a stand, the situation is desperate. However, Kaya herself arrives, intent on bargaining with Kuro.
translations.title: The Silent Man

translations.description: Captain Kuro makes his appearance, and with Zoro too injured to fight, Luffy incapacitated, and Usopp and Nami too weak to make a stand, the situation is desperate. However, Kaya herself arrives, intent on bargaining with Kuro.
translations.title: 音無き男

translations.description: While the fight between Luffy and Kuro continues, Jango is intent on forcing Kaya to bequeath her family's money to the Black Cat captain. Despite the Usopp Pirates' efforts to stop the hypnotist, it seems as if the transaction is all but inevitable.
translations.title: For Whom the Bell Tolls

translations.description: While the fight between Luffy and Kuro continues, Jango is intent on forcing Kaya to bequeath her family's money to the Black Cat captain. Despite the Usopp Pirates' efforts to stop the hypnotist, it seems as if the transaction is all but inevitable.
translations.title: 誰が為に鐘は鳴る

translations.description: Kuro's ultimate move attacks everything in the area, friend nor foe notwithstanding, and Luffy becomes enraged by Kuro's lack of regard for his crew.
translations.title: To the Sea

translations.description: Kuro's ultimate move attacks everything in the area, friend nor foe notwithstanding, and Luffy becomes enraged by Kuro's lack of regard for his crew.
translations.title: 海へ

translations.description: Luffy's fledgling pirate crew arrives at the slopes of Syrup Village. There they find a liar and a conspiracy to steal a young lady's fortune.
translations.title: Syrup Village

translations.description: Luffy's fledgling pirate crew arrives at the slopes of Syrup Village. There they find a liar and a conspiracy to steal a young lady's fortune.
translations.title: シロップ村

translations.description: With Usopp now on the crew and their new ship, the Going Merry, under their command, the Straw Hats head to an island said to hold a fabled treasure. There they encounter a strange man stuck in a box who has been looking for the same treasure.
translations.title: You're the Rare Breed

translations.description: Con Usopp como nuevo miembro de la tripulación y con su nuevo barco bajo su mando, el Going Merry, los Sombrero de Paja se dirigen a una isla que se dice guarda un legendario tesoro. Allí encuentran a un extraño hombre atorado en una caja, que ha estado buscando el mismo tesoro.
translations.title: ¡Eres un animal raro!

translations.description: Avec Usopp maintenant dans l'équipage et leur nouveau navire, le Vogue Merry, les chapeaux de paille se dirigent vers une île censée contenir un trésor légendaire. Là, ils rencontrent un homme étrange coincé dans un coffre qui cherche ce même trésor.
translations.title: Une Faune Insolite

translations.description: With Usopp now on the crew and their new ship, the Going Merry, under their command, the Straw Hats head to an island said to hold a fabled treasure. There they encounter a strange man stuck in a box who has been looking for the same treasure.
translations.title: あんたが珍獣

translations.description: With Usopp now on the crew and their new ship, the Going Merry, under their command, the Straw Hats head to an island said to hold a fabled treasure. There they encounter a strange man stuck in a box who has been looking for the same treasure.
translations.title: Gaimon

translations.description: Con Usopp ahora en la tripulación y un nuevo barco, el Going Merry, a su disposición, los Sombrero de Paja avanzan a la siguiente isla que dicen que tiene un fabuloso tesoro. Allí se encontrarán a un extraño sujeto atascado en una caja, que ha estado buscando el mismo tesoro.
translations.title: Gaimon

translations.description: Avec Usopp maintenant dans l'équipage et leur nouveau navire, le Vogue Merry, sous leur commandement, les Chapeaux de Paille se dirigent vers une île censée contenir un trésor légendaire. C'est sur ces terres qu'ils rencontrent un homme étrange coincé dans une boîte qui cherchait également ce dit trésor.
translations.title: Gaimon

translations.description: With Usopp now on the crew and their new ship, the Going Merry, under their command, the Straw Hats head to an island said to hold a fabled treasure. There they encounter a strange man stuck in a box who has been looking for the same treasure.
translations.title: ガイモン

translations.description: The Straw Hats happen across Zoro's former partners, Yosaku and Johnny, whose dietary dilemma reminds the pirates they still need a cook on their ship. Thus, they set sail for the sea restaurant Baratie, hoping to snag a chef.
translations.title: Enter: Sanji

translations.description: Los Sombrero de Paja se cruzan con los excompañeros de Zoro, Yosaku y Johnny, quienes con su dilema alimenticio les recuerda que aún necesitan un cocinero en su barco. Así, navegan hacia el restaurant marítimo "Baratie", esperando obtener un cocinero.
translations.title: Aparece Sanji

translations.description: The Straw Hats happen across Zoro's former partners, Yosaku and Johnny, whose dietary dilemma reminds the pirates they still need a cook on their ship. Thus, they set sail for the sea restaurant Baratie, hoping to snag a chef.
translations.title: サンジ登場

translations.description: Luffy is on hiatus from pirating to work as a cabin boy to pay off the damage done to the Baratie. While he tries to convince Sanji to join his pirate crew, the pirate Gin brings the infamous Don Krieg and his entire starving fleet to the sea restaurant.
translations.title: Pirate Commodore Don Krieg

translations.description: Luffy en un breve descanso de ser pirata, empieza un trabajo temporal para pagar el daño hecho en el Baratie. Mientras intenta Convencer a Sanji para unirse a su tripulación, Gin, el pirata, trae al infame Don Krieg y su flota figurativamente, flota muerta de hambre al restaurante marino.
translations.title: Don Krieg, el Mayor

translations.description: Luffy is on hiatus from pirating to work as a cabin boy to pay off the damage done to the Baratie. While he tries to convince Sanji to join his pirate crew, the pirate Gin brings the infamous Don Krieg and his entire starving fleet to the sea restaurant.
translations.title: 海賊艦隊提督"首領･クリーク"

translations.description: It's revealed that Chef Zeff was once a great pirate known as "Blaze Leg" Zeff, and his fighting spirit is as strong as ever. Meanwhile, Gin explains how his men met disaster in the Grand Line when they ran afoul of a devastatingly strong opponent.
translations.title: Storm

translations.description: Se revela que el Chef Zeff fue una vez un gran pirata conocido como "Zeff, Pies Rojos", y su espíritu de lucha está más fuerte que nunca. Mientras, Gin explica cómo sus hombres conocieron el horror en el Grand Line cuando por accidente se toparon con un oponente devastadoramente poderoso.
translations.title: Tormenta

translations.description: It's revealed that Chef Zeff was once a great pirate known as "Blaze Leg" Zeff, and his fighting spirit is as strong as ever. Meanwhile, Gin explains how his men met disaster in the Grand Line when they ran afoul of a devastatingly strong opponent.
translations.title: 嵐

translations.description: As Nami steals the Going Merry, Hawk-Eye Mihawk, known far and wide as the world's greatest swordsman, arrives all the way from the Grand Line to finish off Don Krieg. However, Zoro challenges the deadly Mihawk to a duel in order to achieve his dream.
translations.title: The Oath

translations.description: Nami roba el Going Merry, Mihawk Ojo de Halcón, conocido mundialmente como el mejor espadachín, ha llegado desde el Grand Line para acabar con Don Krieg. Sin embargo, Zoro desafía a Mihawk a un duelo mortal para así lograr su sueño.
translations.title: Juramento

translations.description: Alors que Nami vole le Vogue Merry, Œil de Faucon Mihawk, connu comme étant de loin le plus grand épéiste du monde, arrive depuis Grand Line pour achever Don Krieg. Cependant, Zoro défie le dangereux Mihawk en duel afin de réaliser son rêve.
translations.title: Le Serment

translations.description: As Nami steals the Going Merry, Hawk-Eye Mihawk, known far and wide as the world's greatest swordsman, arrives all the way from the Grand Line to finish off Don Krieg. However, Zoro challenges the deadly Mihawk to a duel in order to achieve his dream.
translations.title: 誓い

translations.description: Mihawk departs after defeating Zoro, and Krieg continues his assault on the Baratie. Pearl, one of Krieg's strongest men, goes on the offensive with fiery attacks and multiple shields at his disposal, so Sanji reveals his unique fighting style.
translations.title: Pearl

translations.description: Mihawk departs after defeating Zoro, and Krieg continues his assault on the Baratie. Pearl, one of Krieg's strongest men, goes on the offensive with fiery attacks and multiple shields at his disposal, so Sanji reveals his unique fighting style.
translations.title: Pearl

translations.description: Mihawk se va luego de derrotar a Zoro, y Krieg continúa su asalto al Baratie. Pearl, uno de los hombres más poderosos de la tripulación de Krieg, pasa a la ofensiva con un feroz ataque y múltiples escudos a su disposición, por lo que Sanji revela su estilo de pelea único.
translations.title: Pearl-san

translations.description: Mihawk part après avoir vaincu Zoro, et Krieg continue son assaut sur le Baratie. Pearl, l'un des hommes les plus forts de Krieg, passe à l'offensive avec des attaques enflammées et de multiples boucliers à sa disposition. Sanji révèle alors son style de combat unique.
translations.title: Pearl

translations.description: Mihawk departs after defeating Zoro, and Krieg continues his assault on the Baratie. Pearl, one of Krieg's strongest men, goes on the offensive with fiery attacks and multiple shields at his disposal, so Sanji reveals his unique fighting style.
translations.title: パールさん

translations.description: Sanji continues to battle Pearl, but Gin cleverly holds Chef Zeff hostage, forcing Sanji to let Pearl hit him or lose his mentor for fighting back. Sanji's childhood memories flood his mind, and he reflects on why Zeff means so much to him.
translations.title: Because of a Dream

translations.description: Sanji continue de combattre Pearl, mais Gin tient intelligemment le Chef Zeff en otage, forçant Sanji à laisser Pearl le frapper ou à perdre son mentor s'il riposte. Les souvenirs d'enfance de Sanji inondent son esprit et il réfléchit à la raison pour laquelle Zeff compte tant pour lui.
translations.title: Le Rêve de Deux Hommes

translations.description: Sanji continues to battle Pearl, but Gin cleverly holds Chef Zeff hostage, forcing Sanji to let Pearl hit him or lose his mentor for fighting back. Sanji's childhood memories flood his mind, and he reflects on why Zeff means so much to him.
translations.title: 夢在るがゆえ

translations.description: In a surprising twist, Gin finishes Pearl off himself, claiming Sanji as his own target. Though still wounded, Sanji rises to the challenge and faces off with Gin. As the battle draws to a close, Don Krieg unleashes a deadly toxin into the air.
translations.title: MH5

translations.description: Dans une tournure surprenante, Gin abat Pearl lui-même, revendiquant Sanji comme sa propre cible. Bien que toujours blessé, Sanji relève le défi et affronte Gin. Alors que la bataille touche à sa fin, Don Krieg libère un gaz mortel dans l'air.
translations.title: MH5

translations.description: In a surprising twist, Gin finishes Pearl off himself, claiming Sanji as his own target. Though still wounded, Sanji rises to the challenge and faces off with Gin. As the battle draws to a close, Don Krieg unleashes a deadly toxin into the air.
translations.title: Mエム・Hエイチ・5ファイブ

translations.description: The struggle with Krieg nears its end. Luffy's fighting spirit is unwavering, even after taking several hits from the giant battle spear. Straw Hat’s strategy shifts to smashing through Krieg’s defenses and attacking the spear head-on.
translations.title: The Stalwart War Spear

translations.description: La lutte avec Krieg touche à sa fin. La détermination de Luffy est inébranlable, même après avoir encaissé plusieurs coups de lance. La stratégie du Chapeau de paille lui a permis de passer les défenses de Krieg et de l'attaquer de front.
translations.title: Lance de Guerre

translations.description: The struggle with Krieg nears its end. Luffy's fighting spirit is unwavering, even after taking several hits from the giant battle spear. Straw Hat’s strategy shifts to smashing through Krieg’s defenses and attacking the spear head-on.
translations.title: 大戦槍

translations.description: As dust from the battle settles, Gin, despite still being poisoned, decides to go back to the Grand Line with Krieg, and Sanji makes the difficult decision to join Luffy's crew. Then, Yosaku returns with news of where Nami took the Going Merry.
translations.title: The Fourth

translations.description: Maintenant que la bataille est terminée, Gin, bien qu'il soit toujours empoisonné, décide de retourner sur Grand Line avec Krieg, et Sanji prend la décision difficile de rejoindre l'équipage de Luffy. Par la suite, Yosaku revient avec des nouvelles de l'endroit où Nami est partie avec le Vogue Merry.
translations.title: La Quatrième Recrue

translations.description: As dust from the battle settles, Gin, despite still being poisoned, decides to go back to the Grand Line with Krieg, and Sanji makes the difficult decision to join Luffy's crew. Then, Yosaku returns with news of where Nami took the Going Merry.
translations.title: 4人目

translations.description: The Straw Hats head to the ocean-going restaurant, Baratie, with the hopes of recruiting one of their cooks. In the meantime, hungry yet powerful forces gather to lay siege to the restaurant — all while a menacing swordsman from the Grand Line steadily approaches.
translations.title: Baratie

translations.description: Los Sombrero de Paja parten hacia el restaurante marítimo, Baratie, con la esperanza de reclutar a uno de sus cocineros. Mientras, una hambrienta, pero poderosa fuerza asedia al restaurante cuando un amenazante espadachín del Grand Line se aproxima.
translations.title: Baratie

translations.description: The Straw Hats head to the ocean-going restaurant, Baratie, with the hopes of recruiting one of their cooks. In the meantime, hungry yet powerful forces gather to lay siege to the restaurant — all while a menacing swordsman from the Grand Line steadily approaches.
translations.title: バラティエ

translations.description: As they depart the Baratie in pursuit of Nami and the Going Merry, Yosaku warns Luffy and Sanji about the vicious Arlong and his fishman underlings. Meanwhile, Usopp, Johnny, and Zoro make landfall where Nami docked the Merry.
translations.title: Arlong Park

translations.description: Luego de zarpar del Baratie en búsqueda de Nami y el Going Merry, Yosaku advierte a Luffy y a Sanji del perverso Arlong y su tripulación de Gyojin. Mientras tanto, Usopp, Johnny y Zoro llegan a donde Nami atracó el Merry.
translations.title: Arlong Park

translations.description: As they depart the Baratie in pursuit of Nami and the Going Merry, Yosaku warns Luffy and Sanji about the vicious Arlong and his fishman underlings. Meanwhile, Usopp, Johnny, and Zoro make landfall where Nami docked the Merry.
translations.title: アーロンパーク

translations.description: Usopp, having challenged the fishmen, has been caught. To effectively prove her loyalty to the Arlong Pirates, Nami is left with a morbid choice.
translations.title: Monsters of the Grand Line

translations.description: Usopp es capturado luego de desafiar a los Gyojin. Para probar su lealtad a los Piratas de Arlong, Nami tiene que tomar una mórbida decisión.
translations.title: Monstruos del Grand Line

translations.description: Usopp, having challenged the fishmen, has been caught. To effectively prove her loyalty to the Arlong Pirates, Nami is left with a morbid choice.
translations.title: "偉大なる航路"から来た怪物

translations.description: Luffy’s group has reached the island but are met with a shocking revelation. Unmoved by Nami’s apparent actions and her insistence that he leaves, Luffy stubbornly sticks around.
translations.title: Sea Charts and Fishmen

translations.description: El grupo de Luffy arribó a la isla, pero se encuentran con una impactante revelación. Impasible por el comportamiento de Nami y su insistencia de que se vayan, Luffy obstinadamente decide quedarse.
translations.title: Mapas y Gyojin

translations.description: Luffy’s group has reached the island but are met with a shocking revelation. Unmoved by Nami’s apparent actions and her insistence that he leaves, Luffy stubbornly sticks around.
translations.title: 海図と魚人

translations.description: Nojiko goes into detail about Nami's childhood and their adoptive mother Bell-mère, a former marine. Despite being poor and unrelated by blood, they had a happy life on their tangerine orchard.
translations.title: Bell-mère

translations.description: Nojiko habla en detalle sobre la infancia de Nami y su madre adoptiva Bell-mère, una exmarine. A pesar de haber sido pobres y de no tener relación sanguínea, tuvieron una vida feliz en su huerta de mandarinas.
translations.title: Bell-mère-san

translations.description: Nojiko goes into detail about Nami's childhood and their adoptive mother Bell-mère, a former marine. Despite being poor and unrelated by blood, they had a happy life on their tangerine orchard.
translations.title: ベルメールさん

translations.description: When a Navy officer under Arlong's pay confiscates all the money Nami accumulated over the years, it becomes clear where Arlong stands on his promise.
translations.title: Live

translations.description: Cuando un oficial de la Marina sobornado por Arlong confisca todo el dinero que Nami ha ido acumulando durante años, se vuelve claro dónde está parado Arlong con respecto a su promesa.
translations.title: Vivan

translations.description: When a Navy officer under Arlong's pay confiscates all the money Nami accumulated over the years, it becomes clear where Arlong stands on his promise.
translations.title: 生きる

translations.description: Nami's audible sorrows have reached the ears of a certain Straw Hat captain, and he and his crew rise to action. The villagers look on in awe as the Straw Hats boldly enter Arlong Park to face the fishmen.
translations.title: OK, LET'S STAND UP

translations.description: El llanto de Nami llega a oídos del capitán de los Sombrero de Paja, y él y su tripulación se levantan a luchar. Los aldeanos miran con asombro mientras los Sombrero de Paja entran a Arlong Park para luchar contra los Gyojin.
translations.title: ¡Bien, pongámonos de pie!

translations.description: Nami's audible sorrows have reached the ears of a certain Straw Hat captain, and he and his crew rise to action. The villagers look on in awe as the Straw Hats boldly enter Arlong Park to face the fishmen.
translations.title: OK, Let's STAND UP!

translations.description: Luffy’s newest move leaves him incapacitated and at the mercy of the sea while Zoro, Sanji, and Usopp desperately fight off Arlong’s top officers.
translations.title: Chivalry vs. Fishman Karate

translations.description: El nuevo ataque de Luffy lo deja incapacitado y a merced del mar, mientras Zoro, Sanji y Usopp pelean desesperadamente contra los oficiales de Arlong.
translations.title: Caballerosidad vs. Karate Gyojin

translations.description: Luffy’s newest move leaves him incapacitated and at the mercy of the sea while Zoro, Sanji, and Usopp desperately fight off Arlong’s top officers.
translations.title: 騎士道VS魚人空手

translations.description: The top officers are defeated, but as they currently are, Sanji and Zoro prove to be no match for Arlong. However, with Luffy finally free, he just may just be able to pull it off. Meanwhile, Nami finally gathers the courage to face Arlong.
translations.title: My Turn

translations.description: Los oficiales son derrotados, pero dadas sus condiciones actuales, Zoro y Sanji no pueden plantarse contra Arlong. Pero, ahora que Luffy está libre, podría ser capaz de derrotarlo. Mientras tanto, Nami finalmente encuentra el coraje para enfrentar a Arlong.
translations.title: Mi turno

translations.description: The top officers are defeated, but as they currently are, Sanji and Zoro prove to be no match for Arlong. However, with Luffy finally free, he just may just be able to pull it off. Meanwhile, Nami finally gathers the courage to face Arlong.
translations.title: 交替

translations.description: Luffy springs into action against Arlong, and their intense struggle commences! Luffy becomes enraged when he discovers how exactly Arlong had been using Nami, and he comes to a quick decision on how to finally free her of her shackles.
translations.title: Happiness

translations.description: Luffy salta a la acción y se enfrenta a Arlong, ¡y su intenso combate comienza! Luffy se enfurece cuando descubre de qué manera Arlong ha estado utilizando a Nami, y rápidamente toma una decisión para finalmente liberarla de sus cadenas.
translations.title: Felicidad

translations.description: Luffy springs into action against Arlong, and their intense struggle commences! Luffy becomes enraged when he discovers how exactly Arlong had been using Nami, and he comes to a quick decision on how to finally free her of her shackles.
translations.title: 幸せ

translations.description: Arlong's reign of terror is over, so the island throws a party to celebrate their freedom and to honor their pirate saviors. During the festivities, Nami makes her decision to officially join the Straw Hat Pirates.
translations.title: Spin, Pinwheel, Spin

translations.description: El reino de terror de Arlong ha terminado, y así la isla lanza una fiesta para celebrar su libertad y para festejar a sus salvadores piratas. Durante las festividades, Nami toma la decisión de oficialmente unirse a los Sombrero de Paja.
translations.title: Gira, molino, gira

translations.description: Arlong's reign of terror is over, so the island throws a party to celebrate their freedom and to honor their pirate saviors. During the festivities, Nami makes her decision to officially join the Straw Hat Pirates.
translations.title: まわれ風車

translations.description: Nami's hometown has long been overrun by Arlong and his band of fishmen from the Grand Line. When the Straw Hats arrive, they find that their prospective navigator has left out a few key details about herself.
translations.title: Arlong Park

translations.description: La ciudad natal de Nami ha sido controlada desde hace tiempo por Arlong y su banda de Gyojin (hombres-pez) provenientes del Grand Line. Cuando los Sombrero de Paja llegan, se encuentran que su futura navegante ha dejado atrás unos cuantos detalles clave de sí misma.
translations.title: Arlong Park

translations.description: Nami's hometown has long been overrun by Arlong and his band of fishmen from the Grand Line. When the Straw Hats arrive, they find that their prospective navigator has left out a few key details about herself.
translations.title: アーロンパーク

translations.description: Buggy, after being defeated by Luffy, Zoro, and Nami, begins his quest to regain his body parts and his crew, and then he will get his flashy revenge on Luffy.
translations.title: The Adventures of Buggy's Crew

translations.description: Buggy, luego de ser derrotado por Luffy, Zoro y Nami, empieza su contienda por recuperar sus partes del cuerpo y su tripulación, para poder tener su vistoza venganza contra Luffy.
translations.title: Las aventuras de los Piratas de Buggy

translations.description: Baggy, après avoir été vaincu par Luffy, Zoro et Nami, commence sa quête pour retrouver son équipage et les différentes parties de son corps. Après cela, il pourra se venger en grandes pompes de Luffy.
translations.title: Les Aventures de la Bande à Baggy

translations.description: Touting a fresh bounty issued by Navy HQ, Luffy and co. make landfall at Loguetown, the place where Gold Roger was both born and executed. Being the last stop before the Grand Line, the crew stocks up on supplies and sightsees.
translations.title: The Town of Beginnings and Endings

translations.description: Llevando una nueva recompensa sobre su cabeza emitida por el Cuartel General de la Marina, Luffy y compañía desembarcan en Loguetown, el lugar donde Gold Roger nació y murió. Al ser la última parada antes del Grand Line, la tripulación se abastece de suministros y souvenirs.
translations.title: La ciudad del principio y del fin

translations.description: Touting a fresh bounty issued by Navy HQ, Luffy and co. make landfall at Loguetown, the place where Gold Roger was both born and executed. Being the last stop before the Grand Line, the crew stocks up on supplies and sightsees.
translations.title: 始まりとお 終わりの町

translations.description: Usopp manages to anger the brat daughter of bounty hunter Daddy the Father and finds his own life at stake. When Daddy discovers that Usopp is the son of Red Hair Pirate Yasopp, the only man to beat him, he offers him a risky way out.
translations.title: Parallels

translations.description: Usopp hace enojar a la maleducada hija del cazador de recompensas, Daddy el Padre, y termina con su propia vida en juego. Cuando Daddy descubre que Usopp es hijo de Yasopp, miembro de los Piratas del Pelirrojo y el único hombre que ha conseguido derrotarlo, le ofrece una arriesgada salida a su situación.
translations.title: Paralelismos

translations.description: Usopp manages to anger the brat daughter of bounty hunter Daddy the Father and finds his own life at stake. When Daddy discovers that Usopp is the son of Red Hair Pirate Yasopp, the only man to beat him, he offers him a risky way out.
translations.title: 類似点

translations.description: Luffy finally finds the execution platform, only to be caught in Buggy and Alvida's trap. Sanji and Zoro rush to stop Buggy from poetically executing Luffy where Roger died.
translations.title: The Legend Has Begun

translations.description: Luffy finalmente encuentra la plataforma de ejecución, sólo para caer víctima de la trampa de Buggy y Alvida. Sanji y Zoro se apuran a detener los planes de Buggy antes de que ejecuten a Luffy en el mismo lugar donde murió Roger.
translations.title: La leyenda ha comenzado

translations.description: Luffy finally finds the execution platform, only to be caught in Buggy and Alvida's trap. Sanji and Zoro rush to stop Buggy from poetically executing Luffy where Roger died.
translations.title: 伝説は始まった

translations.description: The final island before entering the Grand Line: Loguetown. Luffy and his crew drop anchor to stock up, sightsee, and pay their respects to the place where Gold Roger drew his last breath.
translations.title: Loguetown

translations.description: La última isla antes de entrar al Grand Line: Loguetown. Luffy y su tripulación tiran anclas para abastecerse, turistear, y rendir honores al lugar donde Gold Roger dejó su último aliento.
translations.title: Loguetown

translations.description: The final island before entering the Grand Line: Loguetown. Luffy and his crew drop anchor to stock up, sightsee, and pay their respects to the place where Gold Roger drew his last breath.

translations.title: リヴァース･マウンテン

translations.description: After learning of Laboon the whale's plight, Luffy comes up with a solution befitting his style. As thanks, Crocus reveals that navigating the Grand Line will not be as simple as following a compass or relying on currents and wind.

translations.description: Reverse Mountain is the entrance to the Grand Line. What await the Straw Hats are impossible water currents, a giant whale, and dubious people going by codenames.

translations.description: The first island on the Grand Line is surprisingly welcoming to pirates. But as night falls, a deadly plot unravels.

translations.title: The Trials of Koby-Meppo

translations.description: Kobby et Hermep sont de nouvelles recrues de la Marine, mais ils sont involontairement impliqués dans une tentative d'évasion de Morgan. Leur courage leur vaudra le respect de leurs supérieurs, ainsi que du Vice-amiral Garp, ou leur coûtera la vie.

translations.description: Los Sombrero de Paja llegan a la siguiente isla, y descubren que es hogar de enormes criaturas... y personas. Mientras tanto, los agentes de Baroque Works, Mr. 3 y su compañera Miss Golden Week, reciben nuevas órdenes.

translations.description: The Straw Hats arrive at their destination and discover that the island is home to enormous creatures... and people. Meanwhile, the Baroque Works agents Mr. 3 and his partner Miss Golden Week receive new orders.
translations.title: 冒険のリトルガーデン

translations.description: Usopp, immensely impressed with the giants of Elbaf, names Brogy his master. To commemorate their duel, the giants imbibe two barrels of booze from Nami, but, unbeknownst to anyone, a saboteur has tampered with one of them!
translations.title: Dorry and Brogy

translations.description: Impresionado por los gigantes de Elbaf, Usopp nombra a Brogy su maestro. Para conmemorar su duelo, los gigantes comparten dos barriles de alcohol que les dio Nami, pero, a sabiendas de nadie, ¡un sabotaje termina dañando a uno de ellos!

translations.title: ドリーとブロギー

translations.description: Despite his internal injuries and Luffy's warnings, the prideful giant Dorry insists on continuing his duel with Brogy. Meanwhile, the Baroque Works officer agents begin to make their move on the island with the Straw Hats as their next targets.
translations.title: Foul Play

translations.description: A pesar de haber sufrido heridas internas y de las advertencias de Luffy, el orgulloso gigante Dorry insiste en continuar su duelo contra Brogy. Mientras tanto, los agentes de Baroque Works comienzan su estrategia en la isla siendo los Sombrero de Paja sus siguientes objetivos.

translations.description: Luffy, Usopp, and Karoo launch headlong into rescuing their friends, but Miss Golden Week runs a colorful interference. Mr. 3 is forced to take matters into his own conniving hands, and Usopp brainstorms how he will finally free his friends.
translations.title: Luffy vs. Mr. 3

translations.description: Luffy, Usopp y Karoo se lanzan de lleno a rescatar a sus amigos, pero Miss Golden Week hace una colorida interferencia. Mr. 3 es forzado a tomar cartas en el asunto, y Usopp tiene una lluvia de ideas sobre cómo podría liberar a sus amigos.
translations.title: Luffy vs. Mr. 3

translations.description: Luffy, Usopp, and Karoo launch headlong into rescuing their friends, but Miss Golden Week runs a colorful interference. Mr. 3 is forced to take matters into his own conniving hands, and Usopp brainstorms how he will finally free his friends.

translations.description: Sanji, pretending to be Mr. 3, convinces Crocodile he has eliminated Vivi and co., prompting the Unluckies to arrive and deliver a way off Little Garden. With a clear path straight ahead—or so it seems—the Straw Hats set sail.
translations.title: Straight Ahead!!

translations.description: Sanji, haciéndose pasar por Mr. 3, convence a Crocodile de que ha eliminado a Vivi y compañía, para dar paso a la llegada de los Unluckies que entregan la salida de Little Garden. Con un claro objetivo que seguir -o así pareciera ser-, los Sombrero de Paja zarpan.
translations.title: ¡Adelante!

translations.description: The Straw Hats vow to bring Princess Vivi to Arabasta, and their journey brings them to Little Garden, an island from prehistoria that is home to creatures and people larger than life.

translations.description: Los Sombrero de Paja juran llevar a la princesa Vivi a Arabasta y su viaje los lleva a Little Garden, una isla prehistórica que alberga a criaturas y personas gigantescas.

translations.description: The Straw Hats vow to bring Princess Vivi to Arabasta, and their journey brings them to Little Garden, an island from prehistoria that is home to creatures and people larger than life.

translations.description: En route to Arabasta, Nami falls ill. Without a doctor aboard the Going Merry, the Straw Hats must decide whether to stay the course or find more immediate help. As their ship crosses into a frigid area, a figure is seen standing on the water's surface.
translations.title: Tin Plate Wapol

translations.description: En camino a Arabasta, Nami cae enferma. Sin un doctor en el barco, los Sombrero de Paja deben decidir si seguir su ruta o si buscar alguna ayuda más inmediata. En tanto su barco cruza un área frígida, una figura se distingue parada en la superficie del mar.
translations.title: Wapol, el hojalata

translations.description: En route pour Alabasta, Nami tombe malade. Sans médecin à bord du Vogue Merry, les Chapeaux de Paille doivent décider de maintenir le cap ou de trouver une aide plus immédiate. Alors que leur navire traverse une zone glaciale, une silhouette est vue à la surface de l'eau.
translations.title: Wapol la Plaque d'Étain

translations.description: En route to Arabasta, Nami falls ill. Without a doctor aboard the Going Merry, the Straw Hats must decide whether to stay the course or find more immediate help. As their ship crosses into a frigid area, a figure is seen standing on the water's surface.
