translations.description: If the Straw Hats have any chance of saving Nami, they must carry her up a mountain to see the sole doctor of a nameless, winter island. While Sanji and Luffy fight off the wilderness, a despicable king makes an unwanted return.
translations.title: Adventure in a Nameless Country

translations.description: Si los Sombrero de Paja tienen alguna oportunidad de salvar a Nami, es cargándola hasta la cima de una montaña para visitar al único doctor de esta isla de invierno sin nombre. Mientras Sanji y Luffy se enfrentan a la vida salvaje, un despreciable rey hace un retorno inoportuno.
translations.title: Aventura en el país sin nombre

translations.description: Si les Chapeaux de Paille veulent avoir une chance de sauver Nami, ils doivent l'emmener sur une montagne pour voir le seul médecin d'une île Hivernale sans nom. Alors que Sanji et Luffy combattent la faune de l'île, un Roi méprisable fait un retour indésirable.
translations.title: À l'Aventure dans un Pays sans nom

translations.description: If the Straw Hats have any chance of saving Nami, they must carry her up a mountain to see the sole doctor of a nameless, winter island. While Sanji and Luffy fight off the wilderness, a despicable king makes an unwanted return.
translations.title: 名もなき国の冒険

translations.description: A devastating avalanche sweeps Drum Island and puts everyone at risk, but Luffy—step-by-step, hand-over-hand—continues his death-defying ascent up the mountain. Meanwhile, Vivi, Usopp, and Zoro reunite in the wake of the disaster.
translations.title: The Summit

translations.description: Una devastadora avalancha arrasa con la Isla de Drum y pone a todos en riesgo, pero Luffy —paso a paso, mano a mano— continúa su ascenso mortal por la montaña. Mientras, Vivi, Usopp y Zoro se reúnen tras el desastre.
translations.title: La cumbre

translations.description: Une avalanche dévastatrice balaie l'île de Drum et met tout le monde en danger, mais Luffy, étape par étape, continue son ascension de la montagne en défiant la mort. Pendant ce temps, Vivi, Usopp et Zoro se réunissent à la suite de la catastrophe.
translations.title: L'Arrivée au Sommet

translations.description: A devastating avalanche sweeps Drum Island and puts everyone at risk, but Luffy—step-by-step, hand-over-hand—continues his death-defying ascent up the mountain. Meanwhile, Vivi, Usopp, and Zoro reunite in the wake of the disaster.
translations.title: 頂上

translations.description: Enter Chopper: a talking, transforming blue-nosed reindeer who was trained by Dr. Kureha in medicine. The Straw Hats immediately see the positives and want him on their crew, but Chopper must first deal with the monstrous pain in his heart.
translations.title: Enter: Tony Tony Chopper

translations.description: Aparece Chopper: un reno de nariz azul que habla, se transforma, y quien fue entrenado en medicina por la Doctora Kureha. Los Sombrero de Paja inmediatamente ven el lado positivo y lo quieren en su tripulación, pero Chopper primero debe luchar contra el monstruoso dolor en su corazón.
translations.title: Aparece Tony Tony Chopper

translations.description: Voici Chopper : un renne au nez bleu qui parle et se transforme, il a été formé par le Dr. Kureha en médecine. Les Chapeaux de Paille y trouvent immédiatement leur compte et le veulent dans leur équipage, mais Chopper doit d'abord faire face à la douleur dans son cœur.
translations.title: Enter: Tony Tony Chopper

translations.description: Enter Chopper: a talking, transforming blue-nosed reindeer who was trained by Dr. Kureha in medicine. The Straw Hats immediately see the positives and want him on their crew, but Chopper must first deal with the monstrous pain in his heart.
translations.title: トニートニー･チョッパー登場

translations.description: Chopper began life as an ordinary reindeer but was shunned by his own kind because of his unusual blue nose. Even after eating the Human-Human Devil Fruit, the islanders wanted nothing to do with him. That is, until Chopper met a certain quack doctor.
translations.title: Quack Doctor

translations.description: Chopper empezó su vida como un reno cualquiera, pero fue rechazado por los de su propia especie debido a su inusual nariz azul. Incluso después de comer la fruta Hito-Hito, los isleños no quisieron saber nada de él. Esto, hasta que Chopper encontró a un disparatado doctor.
translations.title: Curandero

translations.description: Chopper a commencé sa vie comme un renne ordinaire, mais a été rejeté par les siens à cause de son nez bleu inhabituel. Même après avoir mangé le Fruit de l'Humain, les habitants de l'île ne voulaient rien avoir à faire avec lui. C'est jusqu'à ce que Chopper rencontre un certain charlatan.
translations.title: Le Charlatan

translations.description: Chopper began life as an ordinary reindeer but was shunned by his own kind because of his unusual blue nose. Even after eating the Human-Human Devil Fruit, the islanders wanted nothing to do with him. That is, until Chopper met a certain quack doctor.
translations.title: ヤブ医者

translations.description: Wapol and his comrades reach the mountaintop castle to wrest control of it back from Dr. Kureha and Chopper. Luffy, Sanji, and Chopper go head-to-head against his Munch-Munch powers, vowing to keep Wapol and his men from bringing down Hiriluk's flag.
translations.title: Unbreakable

translations.description: Wapol y sus camaradas llegan al castillo en la cima de la montaña para recuperar el control de la Doctora Kureha y Chopper. Luffy, Sanji y Chopper van a enfrentarse contra los poderes de su Baku-Baku, evitando que Wapol y sus hombres derriben la bandera de Hiruluk.
translations.title: Indestructible

translations.description: Wapol et ses subordonnés atteignent le château au sommet de la montagne pour en reprendre le contrôle au Dr. Kureha et à Chopper. Luffy, Sanji et Chopper se battent contre les pouvoirs du Fruit du Glouton, jurant d'empêcher Wapol et ses hommes de faire tomber le drapeau d'Hiluluk.
translations.title: Inébranlable

translations.description: Wapol and his comrades reach the mountaintop castle to wrest control of it back from Dr. Kureha and Chopper. Luffy, Sanji, and Chopper go head-to-head against his Munch-Munch powers, vowing to keep Wapol and his men from bringing down Hiriluk's flag.
translations.title: 折れない

translations.description: Chopper counters the combined Chessmarimo with an item that expands his zoan fruit abilities. Wapol slips away into his old castle, but Luffy runs after him to force a final showdown.
translations.title: The Skies of Drum

translations.description: Chopper contre le Chessmarimo avec un médicament qui étend les capacités de son Fruit du démon. Lorsque Wapol s'éclipse dans son ancien château, Luffy le renverse et le force à un combat final.
translations.title: Le Ciel de Drum

translations.description: Chopper counters the combined Chessmarimo with an item that expands his zoan fruit abilities. Wapol slips away into his old castle, but Luffy runs after him to force a final showdown.
translations.title: ドラムの空

translations.description: Finally convinced to join the Straw Hat Pirates, Chopper announces his intentions to Dr. Kureha. While she doesn’t receive the news well at first, she decides to give the Straw Hats a fond parting gift while they exit the island.
translations.title: Hiriluk's Cherry Blossoms

translations.description: Finalmente convencido de unirse a los piratas del Sombrero de Paja, Chopper anuncia sus intenciones a la Doctora Kureha. Mientras ella no lo acepta de la mejor manera al principio, termina dándole a los Sombrero de Paja un maravilloso regalo mientras huyen de la isla.
translations.title: Las flores de cerezo de Hiluluk

translations.description: Enfin convaincu de rejoindre les Chapeaux de Paille, Chopper annonce ses intentions au Dr. Kureha. Bien qu'elle ne soit pas très ravie au début, elle décide d'offrir un cadeau d'adieu aux Chapeaux de Paille pendant qu'ils quittent l'île.
translations.title: Les Cerisiers de Hiluluk

translations.description: Finally convinced to join the Straw Hat Pirates, Chopper announces his intentions to Dr. Kureha. While she doesn’t receive the news well at first, she decides to give the Straw Hats a fond parting gift while they exit the island.
translations.title: ドラムの空

translations.description: When Nami falls ill, the crew makes a detour from Arabasta to seek medical help. They happen upon a winter island inhabited by a distrusting populace and a single doctor with a mysterious reindeer companion.
translations.title: Drum Island

translations.description: Cuando Nami cae enferma, la tripulación hace un desvío de Arabasta para buscar ayuda médica. Terminando en una isla de invierno habitada por una población desconfiada y una sola doctora con un misterioso reno de compañero.
translations.title: Isla de Drum

translations.description: When Nami falls ill, the crew makes a detour from Arabasta to seek medical help. They happen upon a winter island inhabited by a distrusting populace and a single doctor with a mysterious reindeer companion.
translations.title: ドラム島

translations.description: In Arabasta, the hero Crocodile appears and puts a decisive end to a pillaging band of pirates. Meanwhile, Mr. 2 Bon Kurei pays a visit to the newly arrived Straw Hats. When he puts his abilities on display, Vivi notices something shocking.
translations.title: Sir Crocodile, the Pirate

translations.description: En Arabasta, aparece Crocodile el héroe, y acaba con la banda de piratas saqueadores. En tanto, Mr. 2 Bon Kurei visita a los recién llegados Sombrero de Paja. Mientras hace demostración de sus habilidades, Vivi se da cuenta de algo aterrador.
translations.title: Sir Crocodile, el pirata

translations.description: À Alabasta, le héros Crocodile apparaît et arrête une bande de pirates pilleurs. Pendant ce temps, Mr. 2 Bon Clay rend visite aux Chapeaux de Paille nouvellement arrivés. Quand il expose ses capacités, Vivi remarque quelque chose de choquant.
translations.title: Sir Crocodile, le Pirate

translations.description: In Arabasta, the hero Crocodile appears and puts a decisive end to a pillaging band of pirates. Meanwhile, Mr. 2 Bon Kurei pays a visit to the newly arrived Straw Hats. When he puts his abilities on display, Vivi notices something shocking.
translations.title: "海賊"サー･クロコダイル

translations.description: The Merry makes landfall at Arabasta’s port town, and while the rest of the Straw Hats wisely don disguises, Luffy runs afoul of an old foe. However, a chance reunion with a flame-wielding member of Luffy’s family might just be the saving grace he needs!
translations.title: Landfall in Arabasta

translations.description: El Merry atraca en una ciudad portuaria de Arabasta, y mientras el resto de los Sombrero de Paja inteligentemente buscan disfraces, Luffy se encuentra con un viejo enemigo. A pesar de esto, una afortunada reunión con el llameante miembro de la familia de Luffy podría ser la salvación de último momento que estaba buscando.
translations.title: Llegando a Arabasta

translations.description: Le Merry mouille dans la ville portuaire d'Alabasta, et tandis que le reste des Chapeaux de Paille se déguise judicieusement, Luffy se heurte à un vieil ennemi. Cependant, une réunion familiale fortuite avec un individu maniant les flammes pourrait bien être la grâce salvatrice dont il a besoin !
translations.title: Arrivée à Alabasta

translations.description: The Merry makes landfall at Arabasta’s port town, and while the rest of the Straw Hats wisely don disguises, Luffy runs afoul of an old foe. However, a chance reunion with a flame-wielding member of Luffy’s family might just be the saving grace he needs!
translations.title: 上陸のアラバスタ

translations.description: The Straw Hats finally start their arduous trek across the deserts of Arabasta! Along the way, they encounter martial-arts-loving dugongs, avian con artists, a giant carnivorous reptile, and a camel with very particular tastes in his passengers.
translations.title: Adventure in the Kingdom of Sand

translations.description: ¡Los Sombrero de Paja finalmente comienzan la ardua caminata a través del desierto de Arabasta! En el camino, se encuentran con dugongs amantes de las artes marciales, aves artistas del engaño, un reptil carnívoro gigante, y un camello con un gusto peculiar por sus pasajeros.
translations.title: Aventura en el Reino de la Arena

translations.description: Les Chapeaux de Paille commencent enfin leur périple ardu à travers les déserts d'Alabasta ! En chemin, ils rencontrent des Dugongs amateurs de Kung Fu, des escrocs volants, un reptile carnivore géant et un chameau aux goûts très particuliers chez ses passagers.
translations.title: Aventure au Royaume du Sable

translations.description: The Straw Hats finally start their arduous trek across the deserts of Arabasta! Along the way, they encounter martial-arts-loving dugongs, avian con artists, a giant carnivorous reptile, and a camel with very particular tastes in his passengers.
translations.title: 砂の国の冒険

translations.description: Vivi and co. finally reach Yuba, the last known location of the Rebel Army, but there is nary a soul in sight. Meanwhile, at the behest of their hidden leader, Baroque Works' officer agents begin to gather at the Spiders Cafe.
translations.title: Yuba, the Town of Rebels

translations.description: Vivi y compañía finalmente llegan a Yuba, el último lugar donde se ha visto a la armada rebelde, pero no hay un alma a la vista. Mientras, por solicitud de su líder, los agentes de Baroque Works se empiezan a reunir en el Spider Café.
translations.title: Yuba, el Pueblo de los Rebeldes

translations.description: Vivi and co. finally reach Yuba, the last known location of the Rebel Army, but there is nary a soul in sight. Meanwhile, at the behest of their hidden leader, Baroque Works' officer agents begin to gather at the Spiders Cafe.
translations.title: 反乱軍の町ユバ

translations.description: At Rain Dinners, the Baroque Works officer agents are finally let on to Mr. 0's true identity. And just outside Yuba, Luffy confronts a stubborn Vivi to remind her who else is willing to stand with her.
translations.title: I Love My Country

translations.description: En Rain Dinners, los agentes de Baroque Works finalmente se enteran de la verdadera identidad de Mr. 0. Afuera de Yuba, Luffy enfrenta a una terca Vivi que necesita recordar quienes están dispuestos a luchar junto a ella.
translations.title: Amo mi país

translations.description: At Rain Dinners, the Baroque Works officer agents are finally let on to Mr. 0's true identity. And just outside Yuba, Luffy confronts a stubborn Vivi to remind her who else is willing to stand with her.
translations.title: 国が好き

translations.description: Luffy's band reaches the city of Rainbase but run afoul of Smoker and Tashigi. As they defend themselves against both the Navy and Baroque Works' millions, Luffy's party storms Crocodile's Rain Dinners Casino.
translations.title: Rainbase, the City of Dreams

translations.description: La banda de Luffy llega a la ciudad de Rainbase, pero deben huir de Smoker y Tashigi. Mientras se defienden de los Marinos y los Millions de Baroque Works, Luffy y compañía irrumpen en el Casino de Crocodile "Rain Dinners".
translations.title: Rainbase, la Ciudad de los Sueños

translations.description: Luffy's band reaches the city of Rainbase but run afoul of Smoker and Tashigi. As they defend themselves against both the Navy and Baroque Works' millions, Luffy's party storms Crocodile's Rain Dinners Casino.
translations.title: 夢の町　レインベース

translations.description: Luffy leads a daring—but foolish—raid on Crocodile’s casino. His poor planning lands him behind bars with Captain Smoker. But more importantly, these actions leave Vivi alone and unprotected.
translations.title: It Begins

translations.description: Luffy lidera una intrépida —aunque tonta— travesía en el casino de Crocodile. Su falta de planificación hace que termine detrás de las rejas junto al capitán Smoker. Pero más importante, estas acciones dejan a Vivi sola y desprotegida.
translations.title: Ha comenzado

translations.description: Luffy leads a daring—but foolish—raid on Crocodile’s casino. His poor planning lands him behind bars with Captain Smoker. But more importantly, these actions leave Vivi alone and unprotected.
translations.title: 始まる

translations.description: “The king of Arabasta” appears to order Nanohana’s attack. With this, the people's anger explodes! Meanwhile, Vivi frantically looks for Sanji, and as Crocodile leaves the pirates to their fate, he is suddenly contacted by a "Mr. Prince."
translations.title: Rebellion

translations.description: "El rey de Arabasta" aparece para ordenar un ataque a Nanohana. Con esto, ¡la ira de la gente explota! Mientras, Vivi frenéticamente busca a Sanji, cuando Crocodile deja a los piratas a su suerte, ya que es contactado por un tal "Mr. Prince".
translations.title: Rebelión

translations.description: "Le Roi d'Alabasta" semble ordonner l'attaque de Nanohana. Avec ça, la colère du peuple explose ! Pendant ce temps, Vivi cherche frénétiquement Sanji, et alors que Crocodile laisse les pirates à leur sort, il est soudainement contacté par un "Mr. Prince".
translations.title: Rébellion

translations.description: “The king of Arabasta” appears to order Nanohana’s attack. With this, the people's anger explodes! Meanwhile, Vivi frantically looks for Sanji, and as Crocodile leaves the pirates to their fate, he is suddenly contacted by a "Mr. Prince."
translations.title: 反乱

translations.description: Thanks to Sanji's brave actions, the Straw Hats made their escape, and Captain Smoker graciously looks the other way as they flee. However, as they set out toward Alubarna, Crocodile waylays Luffy, and the two begin a vicious duel.
translations.title: Rush!!

translations.description: Gracias a las heróicas acciones de Sanji, los Sombrero de Paja logran escapar, y el capitán Smoker hace la vista gorda mientras estos huyen. Sin embargo, luego de partir hacia Alubarna, Crocodile asalta a Luffy, por lo que empiezan una feroz batalla.
translations.title: ¡¡Prisa!!

translations.description: Grâce aux actions courageuses de Sanji, les Chapeaux de Paille se sont échappés et le Colonel Smoker regarde gracieusement de l'autre côté alors qu'ils s'enfuient. Cependant, alors qu'ils se dirigent vers Alubarna, Crocodile attaque Luffy et les deux commencent un duel.
translations.title: Rush !!

translations.description: Thanks to Sanji's brave actions, the Straw Hats made their escape, and Captain Smoker graciously looks the other way as they flee. However, as they set out toward Alubarna, Crocodile waylays Luffy, and the two begin a vicious duel.
translations.title: Rush!!

translations.description: Vivi’s party speeds along toward Alubarna, as does the Rebel Army. While the Supersonic Duck Squad helps Zoro and the others play decoy, Vivi sets out on her own to try and stop Koza and his rebels.
translations.title: Showdown at Alubarna

translations.description: El equipo de Vivi se apresura hacia Alubarna, al igual que el ejército rebelde. Mientras el superescuadrón de patos ayuda a Zoro y los demás a ser señuelos, Vivi se va por su cuenta a tratar de detener a Koza y los rebeldes.
translations.title: La batalla decisiva en Alubarna

translations.description: Le groupe de Vivi se dirige vers Alubarna, tout comme l'Armée Rebelle. Alors que l'Escadron des Super Canards aide Zoro et les autres à jouer au leurre, Vivi se lance seule pour essayer d'arrêter Koza et ses rebelles.
translations.title: Bataille décisive à Alubarna

translations.description: Vivi’s party speeds along toward Alubarna, as does the Rebel Army. While the Supersonic Duck Squad helps Zoro and the others play decoy, Vivi sets out on her own to try and stop Koza and his rebels.
translations.title: 決戦はアルバーナ

translations.description: Despite his severe injuries, Karoo picks up Vivi to flee the attacks of Mr. 2, and they dash madly through the battlefield. And at the southeast gate: Chopper and Usopp vs. Mr. 4 and Miss Merry Christmas!
translations.title: Molehill Zone Four

translations.description: Pese a sus graves lesiones, Karoo recoge a Vivi para evitar los ataques de Mr. 2, corriendo desesperadamente a través del campo de batalla. Y en la puerta sureste, ¡Chopper y Usopp contra Mr. 4 y Miss Merry Christmas!
translations.title: Madriguera, Cuarta Manzana

translations.description: Malgré ses blessures graves, Kaloo récupère Vivi pour fuir les attaques de Mr. 2, et ils se précipitent follement à travers le champ de bataille. À la porte sud-est : Chopper et Usopp contre Mr. 4 et Miss Merry Christmas !
translations.title: Taupinière : Quatrième Intersection

translations.description: Despite his severe injuries, Karoo picks up Vivi to flee the attacks of Mr. 2, and they dash madly through the battlefield. And at the southeast gate: Chopper and Usopp vs. Mr. 4 and Miss Merry Christmas!
translations.title: モグラ塚４番街

translations.description: Usopp and Chopper combine their skills to finish off Mr. 4 and Miss Merry Christmas, and Sanji engages Mr. 2 in a vicious foot-to-foot struggle. Meanwhile, as a last-ditch effort to save her people, Princess Vivi gives Chaka an unprecedented order.
translations.title: Okama Kenpo

translations.description: Usopp y Chopper combinan sus ataques para acabar con Mr. 4 y Miss Merry Christmas, y Sanji arremete contra Mr. 2 en una feroz lucha pie a pie. Mientras, en un último esfuerzo desesperado para salvar a su gente, la princesa Vivi le da a Chaka una orden sin precedentes.
translations.title: Okama Kenpo

translations.description: Usopp et Chopper combinent leurs compétences pour achever Mr. 4 et Miss Merry Christmas. Sanji engage Mr. 2 dans une lutte de jambes acharnée. Pendant ce temps, dans un ultime effort pour sauver son peuple, la princesse Vivi donne à Chaka un ordre sans précédent.
translations.title: Le Coup de Ballet

translations.description: Usopp and Chopper combine their skills to finish off Mr. 4 and Miss Merry Christmas, and Sanji engages Mr. 2 in a vicious foot-to-foot struggle. Meanwhile, as a last-ditch effort to save her people, Princess Vivi gives Chaka an unprecedented order.
translations.title: オカマ拳法

translations.description: Nami combats Miss Doublefinger, whose Spike-Spike powers quickly turn their brawl into a losing battle. That is, until Usopp's invention, the Clima-Tact, gives Nami a fighting chance. And at the palace, Crocodile reveals his ultimate goal.
translations.title: She Who Controls the Weather

translations.description: Nami combate contra Miss Doublefinger, quien con su poder Toge Toge rápidamente vuelve esta lucha en una batalla perdida. Hasta que el invento de Usopp, el Clima Tact, le da a Nami una oportunidad de pelear. En el palacio, Crocodile revela su meta final.
translations.title: La mujer que controla el clima

translations.description: Nami affronte Miss Doublefinger, dont son Fruit de l'Oursin transforme rapidement leur bagarre en une bataille perdue d'avance. C'est jusqu'à ce que l'invention d'Usopp, le Clima-Tact, donne à Nami une chance de se battre. Au palais, Crocodile révèle alors son but ultime.
translations.title: La Maîtresse du Climat

translations.description: Nami combats Miss Doublefinger, whose Spike-Spike powers quickly turn their brawl into a losing battle. That is, until Usopp's invention, the Clima-Tact, gives Nami a fighting chance. And at the palace, Crocodile reveals his ultimate goal.
translations.title: 天候を操る女

translations.description: Crocodile reveals he seeks the mysterious Pluton, Nami has one last chance to stop Miss Doublefinger, and Zoro struggles against Mr. 1. As Zoro confronts certain death, he must remember something his sensei once imparted.
translations.title: Cutting Steel

translations.description: Crocodile revela que busca al misterioso Pluton, Nami tiene una última oportunidad de detener a Miss Doublefinger, y Zoro lucha contra Mr. 1. Mientras Zoro se enfrenta a una muerte segura, debe recordar algo que su sensei una vez le enseñó.
translations.title: Cortando el acero

translations.description: Crocodile révèle qu'il cherche la mystérieuse arme Pluton. Nami a une dernière chance d'arrêter Miss Doublefinger et Zoro se bat contre Mr. 1. Alors que notre sabreur fait face à une mort certaine, il doit se souvenir de quelque chose que son maître lui a une fois confié.
translations.title: Fendre l'Acier

translations.description: Crocodile reveals he seeks the mysterious Pluton, Nami has one last chance to stop Miss Doublefinger, and Zoro struggles against Mr. 1. As Zoro confronts certain death, he must remember something his sensei once imparted.
translations.title: 鉄を斬る

translations.description: Vivi reveals Crocodile's heinous plan to Koza. To stop the fighting, Koza raises the white flag but is suddenly shot. To induce even more panic, Crocodile announces that a massive bomb will be launched into the city, and he drops Vivi to her doom.
translations.title: The Leaders

translations.description: Vivi révèle le plan odieux de Crocodile à Koza. Pour arrêter les combats, Koza lève le drapeau blanc mais est soudainement abattu. Pour provoquer encore plus de panique, Crocodile annonce qu'une énorme bombe sera lancée sur la ville, et il laisse tomber Vivi à sa perte.
translations.title: L'Unificateur

translations.description: Vivi reveals Crocodile's heinous plan to Koza. To stop the fighting, Koza raises the white flag but is suddenly shot. To induce even more panic, Crocodile announces that a massive bomb will be launched into the city, and he drops Vivi to her doom.
translations.title: 統率者達

translations.description: Luffy vs. Crocodile: Round 2! Luffy has discovered Crocodile’s weakness, but the power of the Sand-Sand Fruit is devastating regardless. Meanwhile, the remaining Straw Hats have 10 minutes find a hidden cannoneer before a bomb is launched into the city.
translations.title: Hope!

translations.description: Luffy vs. Crocodile: ¡Segunda ronda! Luffy ha descubierto la debilidad de Crocodile, pero los poderes de la fruta Suna-Suna sigue siendo devastadora. Mientras, el resto de los Sombrero de paja tienen 10 minutos para encontrar al cañonero oculto antes de que la bomba sea lanzada a la ciudad.
translations.title: ¡Esperanza!

translations.description: Luffy VS. Crocodile : 2e round ! Luffy a découvert la faiblesse de Crocodile, mais le pouvoir du Fruit des Sables est dévastateur malgré tout. Pendant ce temps, les Chapeaux de Paille ont 10 minutes pour trouver un canonnier caché, avant qu'une bombe n'explose sur la ville.
translations.title: Espoir !!

translations.description: Luffy vs. Crocodile: Round 2! Luffy has discovered Crocodile’s weakness, but the power of the Sand-Sand Fruit is devastating regardless. Meanwhile, the remaining Straw Hats have 10 minutes find a hidden cannoneer before a bomb is launched into the city.
translations.title: HOPEホープ!!

translations.description: Luffy and Crocodile enter the third phase of their duel, and, without water at his disposal, Luffy is forced to improvise. Back on the surface, Vivi uses her knowledge of the city to finally pinpoint the location of the bomb's cannoneer.
translations.title: Croc-ish

translations.description: Luffy y Crocodile entran en la tercera fase del combate y, sin agua a su disposición, Luffy es forzado a improvisar. En la superficie, Vivi usa su conocimiento de la ciudad para finalmente encontrar la ubicación del cañonero de la bomba.
translations.title: Cocodrilesco

translations.description: Luffy et Crocodile entrent dans la 3e phase de leur duel, et, sans eau à sa disposition, Luffy est obligé d'improviser. De retour à la surface, Vivi utilise sa connaissance de la ville pour enfin localiser la bombe.
translations.title: Ça sent le croco

translations.description: Luffy and Crocodile enter the third phase of their duel, and, without water at his disposal, Luffy is forced to improvise. Back on the surface, Vivi uses her knowledge of the city to finally pinpoint the location of the bomb's cannoneer.
translations.title: ワニっぽい

translations.description: Vivi finds the cannon but realizes the bomb can't be stopped so casually. Then Pell swoops in with a decisive, if tragic, solution. The final battle between Luffy and Crocodile, which has both parties driven to their utmost, reaches its conclusion.
translations.title: I Will Defeat You

translations.description: Vivi encuentra el cañón, pero se da cuenta que la bomba no puede ser detenida tan fácilmente. Entonces Pell, decide tomar una decisiva, pero trágica solución. El duelo final entre Luffy y Crocodile, que tiene a ambos dando todo de sí, llega a su conclusión.
translations.title: Superarte

translations.description: Vivi trouve le canon mais se rend compte que la bombe ne peut pas être arrêtée aussi facilement. Puis Pell se précipite avec une solution décisive, bien que tragique. La bataille finale entre Luffy et Crocodile, qui les a poussé à leur maximum, touche à sa fin.
translations.title: Surpasser

translations.description: Vivi finds the cannon but realizes the bomb can't be stopped so casually. Then Pell swoops in with a decisive, if tragic, solution. The final battle between Luffy and Crocodile, which has both parties driven to their utmost, reaches its conclusion.
translations.title: 超えて行く

translations.description: Igaram appears with proof of Cobra's innocence, and Koza tells the people the truth behind the war. Luffy and his crew are brought into Cobra's palace to rest, and, during this time, Igaram receives word that there are new bounties making the rounds!
translations.title: Some Justice

translations.description: Igaram aparece con pruebas de la inocencia de Cobra, y Koza le cuenta la verdad detrás de la guerra a la gente. Luffy y su tripulación es llevado al palacio de Cobra para descansar, y durante este tiempo, ¡Igaram recibe noticias de sus nuevas recompensas!
translations.title: Un poco de justicia

translations.description: Igaram apparaît avec la preuve de l'innocence de Cobra et Koza révèle au peuple la vérité derrière la guerre. Luffy et son équipage sont amenés dans le palais de Cobra pour se reposer, et pendant ce temps, Igaram apprend qu'il y a de nouvelles primes qui font le tour !
translations.title: La Justice à plusieurs facettes !

translations.description: Igaram appears with proof of Cobra's innocence, and Koza tells the people the truth behind the war. Luffy and his crew are brought into Cobra's palace to rest, and, during this time, Igaram receives word that there are new bounties making the rounds!
translations.title: いくつかの正義

translations.description: As the Straw Hats make their escape from Arabasta, Bon Kurei and his men serve to distract Black Cage Hina of the Navy. Meanwhile, Vivi must make a speech, but, more importantly, she must decide whether to stay with the Straw Hats.
translations.title: Vivi's Adventure

translations.description: Mientras los Sombrero de Paja escapan de Arabasta, Bon Kurei y sus hombres se sacrifican para distraer a Hina "Jaula Negra" de la Marina. Mientras, Vivi debe dar un discurso, pero más importante, debe decidir si se va a quedar o se irá con los Sombrero de Paja.
translations.title: La aventura de Vivi

translations.description: Alors que les Chapeaux de Paille s'échappent d'Alabasta, Bon Clay et ses hommes distraient Hina la Cage Noire, une Contre-Amirale de la Marine. Pendant ce temps, Vivi doit faire un discours, mais, plus important encore, elle doit décider si elle doit rester avec les Chapeaux de Paille ou non.
translations.title: L'Aventure de Vivi

translations.description: As the Straw Hats make their escape from Arabasta, Bon Kurei and his men serve to distract Black Cage Hina of the Navy. Meanwhile, Vivi must make a speech, but, more importantly, she must decide whether to stay with the Straw Hats.
translations.title: ビビの冒険

translations.description: The Straw Hats have evaded the marines, but a new development crops up when a certain stowaway makes her presence on the Going Merry known… and she wants to be part of the crew!
translations.title: Stowaway

translations.description: Los Sombrero de Paja han evadido a los marinos, pero un nuevo suceso aparece cuando cierta polizona hace presencia en el Going Merry... ¡y quiere ser parte de la tripulación!
translations.title: Polizón

translations.description: Les Chapeaux de Paille ont échappé aux marines, mais un nouveau problème surgit lorsqu'un certain passager clandestin fait connaître sa présence sur le Vogue Merry... et elle veut faire partie de l'équipage !
translations.title: Une Clandestine à Bord

translations.description: The Straw Hats have evaded the marines, but a new development crops up when a certain stowaway makes her presence on the Going Merry known… and she wants to be part of the crew!
translations.title: 密航者

translations.description: Arabasta teeters on the edge of civil war, and it's up to Princess Vivi and the Straw Hats to stem the rebellion, uncover the plot of Baroque Works, and beat the Warlord Crocodile.
translations.title: Arabasta

translations.description: Arabasta está al borde de una guerra civil, y depende de la princesa Vivi y los Sombrero de Paja apaciguar la rebelión, revelar el complot de Baroque Works, y derrotar al Shichibukai Crocodile.
translations.title: Arabasta

translations.description: Alabasta est au bord de la guerre civile, et c'est à la princesse Vivi et aux Chapeaux de Paille d'empêcher la rébellion, de découvrir ce que complote le Baroque Works et de battre Crocodile, le Grand Corsaire.
translations.title: Alabasta

translations.description: Arabasta teeters on the edge of civil war, and it's up to Princess Vivi and the Straw Hats to stem the rebellion, uncover the plot of Baroque Works, and beat the Warlord Crocodile.
translations.title: アラバスタ王国

translations.description: When a galleon-size ship falls from the sky and Nami's log pose begins to point straight up, the Straw Hats sense a new adventure on the horizon. Right after a mysterious map is pulled from the wreckage, a group of salvagers come to claim the fallen ship.
translations.title: Why the Log Pose Is Spherical

translations.description: Cuando un barco del tamaño de un galeón cae desde el cielo y el Log Pose de Nami empieza a apuntar hacia arriba, los Sombrero de Paja perciben una nueva aventura en el horizonte. Justo después de que un misterioso mapa es retirado de los escombros, un grupo de rescatistas vienen a reclamar el barco caído.
translations.title: Por qué el Log Pose es esférico

translations.description: Lorsqu'un navire de la taille d'un galion tombe du ciel et que l'aiguille du Log Pose de Nami commence à pointer vers le haut, les Chapeaux de Paille sentent une nouvelle aventure à l'horizon. Juste après qu'une carte mystérieuse ait été retirée de l'épave du galion, un groupe de sauveteurs vient récupérer le navire tombé.
translations.title: Pourquoi le Log Pose est une Sphère

translations.description: When a galleon-size ship falls from the sky and Nami's log pose begins to point straight up, the Straw Hats sense a new adventure on the horizon. Right after a mysterious map is pulled from the wreckage, a group of salvagers come to claim the fallen ship.
translations.title: 「記録指針」が丸い理由

translations.description: Mock Town on western Jaya openly welcomes pirates, but that fact is accompanied by constant danger. While asking about the sky island, Luffy and Zoro have a run-in with the loud pirate Bellamy the Hyena who ridicules their dreams.
translations.title: Never Dream

translations.description: Mock Town, un pueblo en el lado oeste de Jaya no tiene tapujos en dar la bienvenida a los piratas, pero este hecho viene con un constante peligro. Mientras preguntaban por la isla en el cielo, Luffy y Zoro tienen un encontrón con el molesto pirata Bellamy la Hiena, quien ridiculiza sus sueños.
translations.title: Nunca sueñes

translations.description: Mock Town on western Jaya openly welcomes pirates, but that fact is accompanied by constant danger. While asking about the sky island, Luffy and Zoro have a run-in with the loud pirate Bellamy the Hyena who ridicules their dreams.
translations.title: 夢を見るな

translations.description: After a one-sided brawl with Bellamy, the Straw Hats meet a black-haired pirate outside the bar who reaffirms their dreams and insists the sky island is real. As they depart for the other side of Jaya, another salvager of the Saruyama Alliance appears.
translations.title: People's Dreams

translations.description: Luego de una batalla en la que sólo Bellamy peleaba, los Sombrero de Paja se encuentran con un pirata de pelo negro afuera del bar, quien reafirma sus sueños e insiste en que la Isla del Cielo es real. Mientras se marchan desde el otro lado de Jaya, otro rescatador de la Alianza Saruyama aparece.
translations.title: Los sueños del hombre

translations.description: Après une bagarre unilatérale avec Bellamy, les Chapeaux de Paille rencontrent un pirate aux cheveux noirs à l'extérieur du bar qui réaffirme leurs rêves et insiste sur le fait que l'île céleste existe. Alors qu'ils partent pour l'autre côté de Jaya, un autre sauveteur de la Ligue des Primates apparaît.
translations.title: Les Rêves

translations.description: After a one-sided brawl with Bellamy, the Straw Hats meet a black-haired pirate outside the bar who reaffirms their dreams and insists the sky island is real. As they depart for the other side of Jaya, another salvager of the Saruyama Alliance appears.
translations.title: 人の夢

translations.description: The Straw Hats meet Montblanc Cricket, whose descendant was none other than Montblanc Noland, an infamous "liar" who told of a city of gold on Jaya. Cast out for looking for artifacts from the fabled city, he may just know a way to get to Skypiea.
translations.title: Noland the Liar

translations.description: Los Sombrero de Paja conocen a Montblanc Cricket, quien es descendiente de nadie más que Montblanc Noland, un infame "mentiroso" que hablaba de una ciudad de oro en Jaya. Buscando artefactos de esta ciudad que parece de fábulas, él podría conocer una forma de llegar a Skypiea.
translations.title: Noland, el Mentiroso

translations.description: Les Chapeaux de Paille rencontrent Montblanc Cricket, dont le descendant n'était autre que Montblanc Norland, un "menteur" tristement célèbre qui a parlé d'une ville d'or sur Jaya. Chasse à la recherche d'artefacts de la ville légendaire, il connaît peut-être un moyen de se rendre à Skypiea.
translations.title: Norland, le Roi des Menteurs

translations.description: The Straw Hats meet Montblanc Cricket, whose descendant was none other than Montblanc Noland, an infamous "liar" who told of a city of gold on Jaya. Cast out for looking for artifacts from the fabled city, he may just know a way to get to Skypiea.
translations.title: うそつきノーランド

translations.description: Cricket explains how the Straw Hats can ride a dangerous vertical sea current to get to Skypiea. However, they must first catch a south bird to steer them toward the point where the stream will erupt from the ocean.
translations.title: Let's Eat

translations.description: Cricket le explica a los Sombrero de Paja como podrían montar una peligrosa corriente vertical para poder llegar hasta Skypiea. Sin embargo, primero deben capturar a una ave del sur, para que puedan dirigirse al punto en que la corriente erupcionará desde el mar.
translations.title: ¡A comer!

translations.description: Cricket explique comment les Chapeaux de Paille peuvent chevaucher un dangereux courant marin vertical pour se rendre à Skypiea. Cependant, ils doivent d'abord attraper un South Bird pour les diriger vers le point où le ruisseau jaillira de l'océan.
translations.title: À table !

translations.description: Cricket explains how the Straw Hats can ride a dangerous vertical sea current to get to Skypiea. However, they must first catch a south bird to steer them toward the point where the stream will erupt from the ocean.
translations.title: メシを食おう

translations.description: While the Straw Hats are in the forest attempting to catch a south bird, Bellamy and his crew attack Masira, Shoujou, and Cricket and steal every gold artifact they had collected over the years from the salvage work of the Saruyama Alliance.
translations.title: The Hundred Million Man

translations.description: Mientras los Sombero de Paja están en el bosque tratando de capturar al pajaro del sur, Bellamy y su tripulación atacan a Masira, Shoujou y a Cricket, robándoles cada artefacto de oro que han recolectado durante años con su salvaje Alianza Saruyama.
translations.title: El hombre de los 100 millones

translations.description: Alors que les Chapeaux de Paille sont dans la forêt pour tenter d'attraper un South Bird, Bellamy et son équipage attaquent Masira, Shôjô et Cricket et volent tous les artéfacts en or qu'ils avaient collectés au fil des années lors du travail de récupération de la Ligue des Primates.
translations.title: L'Homme qui valait 100 Millions

translations.description: While the Straw Hats are in the forest attempting to catch a south bird, Bellamy and his crew attack Masira, Shoujou, and Cricket and steal every gold artifact they had collected over the years from the salvage work of the Saruyama Alliance.
translations.title: 一億の男

translations.description: The duel between Bellamy and Luffy shocks all who look on. More shocking are the movements of fearsome pirates on the Grand Line and the machinations of the Blackbeard Pirates, as their captain vies for a position as a warlord.
translations.title: The Highest Authority in the World

translations.description: El duelo entre Bellamy y Luffy impacta a todo quien lo ve. Más sorprendente son los movimientos de los temibles piratas en el Grand Line y las maquinaciones de los Piratas de Barbanegra, ya que su capitán busca tener un puesto en los Ouka Shichibukai.
translations.title: La autoridad más alta del mundo

translations.description: Le duel entre Bellamy et Luffy choque tous ceux qui regardent. Plus choquantes sont les actions de redoutables pirates sur Grand Line et les machinations des pirates de Barbe Noire, alors que leur capitaine se dispute un poste de Grand Corsaire.
translations.title: La plus Grande Instance au Monde

translations.description: The duel between Bellamy and Luffy shocks all who look on. More shocking are the movements of fearsome pirates on the Grand Line and the machinations of the Blackbeard Pirates, as their captain vies for a position as a warlord.
translations.title: 世界最高権力

translations.description: Luffy returns victorious from his showdown with Bellamy, and the Going Merry has been refit by the Saruyama Alliance to handle its upcoming upward flight. The Straw Hats follow their captive south bird and steel themselves for their journey to the sky.
translations.title: The Knock-Up Stream

translations.description: Luffy vuelve victorioso del encuentro con Bellamy, y el Going Merry ha sido ajustado por la Alianza Saruyama para que pueda ser controlado en el vuelo vetical que va a vivir. Los Sombrero de Paja siguen a su pajaro del sur y se arman de valor para su viaje a la Isla del Cielo.
translations.title: El Knock-Up Stream

translations.description: Luffy revient victorieux de son affrontement avec Bellamy, et le Vogue Merry a été réaménagé par la Ligue des Primates pour gérer son prochain vol ascendant. Les Chapeaux de Paille suivent leur South Bird capturé et se préparent pour leur voyage vers le ciel.
translations.title: Le Knock-Up Stream

translations.description: Luffy returns victorious from his showdown with Bellamy, and the Going Merry has been refit by the Saruyama Alliance to handle its upcoming upward flight. The Straw Hats follow their captive south bird and steel themselves for their journey to the sky.
translations.title: 突き上げる海流

translations.description: The Straw Hats seek the fabled sky island Skypiea and head to Jaya for information on its whereabouts. Their convictions are tested by the pirates of Mock Town, but not everyone on the island is a hardline skeptic.
translations.title: Jaya

translations.description: Los Sombrero de Paja buscan la fantástica isla en el cielo, Skypiea, y se dirigen a Jaya para buscar información de dónde se encuentra. Sus convicciones son puestas a prueba por los piratas de Mock Town, pero no todos en la isla son tan escépticos.
translations.title: Jaya

translations.description: The Straw Hats seek the fabled sky island Skypiea and head to Jaya for information on its whereabouts. Their convictions are tested by the pirates of Mock Town, but not everyone on the island is a hardline skeptic.
translations.title: ジャヤ

translations.description: The Straw Hats, having used the Knock-Up Stream to fly into the sky, arrive on a white ocean above the clouds. While they marvel at the otherworldly sights, they are attacked by a powerful masked figure, and a mysterious flying knight comes to their aid.
translations.title: Heaven's Gate

translations.description: Los Sombrero de Paja, luego de haber usado el Knock-Up Stream para volar al cielo, llegan a un océano blanco sobre las nubes. Mientras se maravillan por los indescriptibles paisajes, son atacados por una poderosa figura enmascarada, para ser rescatados por un misterioso Caballero del Cielo.
translations.title: La Puerta del Cielo

translations.description: Les Chapeaux de Paille, ayant utilisé le Knock-up Stream pour voler dans le ciel, arrivent sur un océan blanc au-dessus des nuages. Alors qu'ils s'émerveillent devant les paysages d'un autre monde, ils sont attaqués par une puissante personne masquée, et un mystérieux chevalier volant leur vient en aide.
translations.title: La Porte du Paradis

translations.description: The Straw Hats, having used the Knock-Up Stream to fly into the sky, arrive on a white ocean above the clouds. While they marvel at the otherworldly sights, they are attacked by a powerful masked figure, and a mysterious flying knight comes to their aid.
translations.title: 天国の門

translations.description: After bidding farewell to Gan Fall and passing through the gate to Skypiea, the pirates encounter a family of Skypieans: Conis and her father, Pagaya. The two explain the workings of life in the sky and introduce the crew to the different dials.
translations.title: Angel Beach

translations.description: Luego de despedirse de Gan Fall y pasar por la entrada de Skypiea, los piratas encuentran una familia de Skypieans: Conis y su padre Pagaya. Los dos les explican las costumbres de la vida en el cielo y presentan a la tripulación los diferentes dials.
translations.title: Angel Beach

translations.description: Après avoir fait ses adieux à Gan Forr et passé la porte de Skypiea, les pirates rencontrent une famille de Skypiéns : Conis et son père Pagaya. Les deux expliquent le fonctionnement de la vie dans le ciel et présentent à l'équipage les différents Dials.
translations.title: Angel Beach

translations.description: After bidding farewell to Gan Fall and passing through the gate to Skypiea, the pirates encounter a family of Skypieans: Conis and her father, Pagaya. The two explain the workings of life in the sky and introduce the crew to the different dials.
translations.title: エンジェルビーチ

translations.description: Nami takes the waver out for a test ride and discovers the forbidden Upper Yard. Meanwhile, law enforcement arrives and rudely harasses the rest of the gang.
translations.title: Divine Reckoning

translations.description: Nami toma prestado un waver para probarlo y descubre la prohibida Upper Yard. Mientras tanto, las fuerzas de la ley aparecen y comienzan a molestar a la tripulación.
translations.title: El Juicio del Cielo

translations.description: Nami prend le waver pour un essai et découvre l'Upper Yard interdit. Pendant ce temps, le reste de la bande attend que le vent change pour pouvoir être en route, mais les forces de l'ordre arrivent et harcèlent brutalement l'équipage.
translations.title: Le Jugement Céleste

translations.description: Nami takes the waver out for a test ride and discovers the forbidden Upper Yard. Meanwhile, law enforcement arrives and rudely harasses the rest of the gang.
translations.title: 天の裁き

translations.description: The pirates are fed up and ready to leave Skypiea, but Nami, Zoro, Robin, and Chopper are whisked away aboard the Merry. The remaining Straw Hat Pirates must face Enel’s challenge, so Conis shows them the way to Upper Yard.
translations.title: Ordeal

translations.description: Los piratas comen algo y se preparan para dejar Skypiea, pero Nami, Zoro, Robin y Chopper son tomados rehenes a bordo del Merry. Los Sombrero de Paja restantes deben enfrentar el desafío de Enel, entonces Conis les muestra el camino hacia Upper Yard.
translations.title: Prueba

translations.description: Les pirates en ont assez et sont prêts à quitter Skypiea, mais Nami, Zoro, Robin et Chopper sont emmenés à bord du Merry. Les Chapeaux de Paille restants doivent relever le défi d'Ener, alors Conis leur montre le chemin vers Upper Yard.
translations.title: L'Ordalie

translations.description: The pirates are fed up and ready to leave Skypiea, but Nami, Zoro, Robin, and Chopper are whisked away aboard the Merry. The remaining Straw Hat Pirates must face Enel’s challenge, so Conis shows them the way to Upper Yard.
translations.title: 試練

translations.description: Aboard the Little Crow, Luffy, Usopp, and Sanji enter Upper Yard and must choose an ordeal. Meanwhile, Zoro and co. have their own troubles at the Sacrificial Altar. When they leave to explore the forest, Chopper is left to repair the Merry.
translations.title: Adventure on God's Island

translations.description: À bord du Corbeau, Luffy, Usopp et Sanji entrent dans Upper Yard et doivent choisir une épreuve. Pendant ce temps, Zoro et compagnie ont leurs propres problèmes à l'Autel sacrificiel. Quand ils partent explorer la forêt, Chopper, lui, doit rester pour réparer le Merry.
translations.title: À l'Aventure en Terre Divine

translations.description: Aboard the Little Crow, Luffy, Usopp, and Sanji enter Upper Yard and must choose an ordeal. Meanwhile, Zoro and co. have their own troubles at the Sacrificial Altar. When they leave to explore the forest, Chopper is left to repair the Merry.
translations.title: 神の島の冒険

translations.description: Luffy, Sanji, and Usopp are locked in a life-or-death struggle against the Priest Satori. It's all they can do to withstand the random attributes of Satori's strange spheres and to overcome the power of mantra, which can seemingly predict their movements.
translations.title: The Village Hidden in the Clouds

translations.description: Luffy, Sanji, and Usopp are locked in a life-or-death struggle against the Priest Satori. It's all they can do to withstand the random attributes of Satori's strange spheres and to overcome the power of mantra, which can seemingly predict their movements.
translations.title: 雲隠れの村

translations.description: Gan Fall is severely burned during his battle with Shura, and Chopper musters the courage for a leap of faith. Elsewhere, Luffy and co. finally discover a way to defeat the mantra-wielding Satori, and the Shandians prepare for an all-out attack on God!
translations.title: Overture

translations.description: Gan Fall is severely burned during his battle with Shura, and Chopper musters the courage for a leap of faith. Elsewhere, Luffy and co. finally discover a way to defeat the mantra-wielding Satori, and the Shandians prepare for an all-out attack on God!
translations.title: 序曲(オーバーチュア)

translations.description: The Shandians’ attack on Upper Yard commences! At the Sacrificial Altar, the crew is finally reunited, and everyone recounts what has happened. Chopper looks after the injured Gan Fall, and the pirates devise a plan to steal the gold on the island.
translations.title: Vearth

translations.description: The Shandians’ attack on Upper Yard commences! At the Sacrificial Altar, the crew is finally reunited, and everyone recounts what has happened. Chopper looks after the injured Gan Fall, and the pirates devise a plan to steal the gold on the island.
translations.title: ヴァース

translations.description: The crew splits up into Nami's escape team and Luffy's exploration team. Unfortunately, a giant snake attacks and separates Luffy's team. To top it all off, the Priests have set up their ordeals across the whole island.
translations.title: Dial Battle

translations.description: The crew splits up into Nami's escape team and Luffy's exploration team. Unfortunately, a giant snake attacks and separates Luffy's team. To top it all off, the Priests have set up their ordeals across the whole island.
translations.title: 貝ダイアルバトル

translations.description: Only 80 remain in the Upper Yard survival game. Zoro finds himself face-to-face with the Shandian Braham, Luffy takes on Wyper and his burning bazooka, and Nami’s group on the Merry has the deadliest encounter of all!
translations.title: Pirate Luffy vs. Berserker Wyper

translations.description: Only 80 remain in the Upper Yard survival game. Zoro finds himself face-to-face with the Shandian Braham, Luffy takes on Wyper and his burning bazooka, and Nami’s group on the Merry has the deadliest encounter of all!
translations.title: 海賊ルフィ vs 戦鬼ワイパー

translations.description: Luffy's fight with Wyper lands him in a dark cavern filled with ruins, Enel leaves a deadly pair of new enemies to deal with Nami and Gan Fall, and Chopper comes face to face with Sky Punk Gedatsu.
translations.title: Pirate Chopper vs. Priest Gedatsu

translations.description: Luffy's fight with Wyper lands him in a dark cavern filled with ruins, Enel leaves a deadly pair of new enemies to deal with Nami and Gan Fall, and Chopper comes face to face with Sky Punk Gedatsu.
translations.title: 海賊チョッパー vs 神官ゲダツ

translations.description: Enel continues his attack, wiping out several fighters regardless of their allegiance. An hour remains until Enel's deadline, and only 24 survivors remain. Meanwhile, after a deadly struggle with the rotund Yama, Robin makes the discovery of a lifetime.
translations.title: Pirate Robin vs. Commander Yama

translations.description: Enel continues his attack, wiping out several fighters regardless of their allegiance. An hour remains until Enel's deadline, and only 24 survivors remain. Meanwhile, after a deadly struggle with the rotund Yama, Robin makes the discovery of a lifetime.
translations.title: 海賊ロビン vs 神兵長ヤマ

translations.description: While Luffy remains lost in a strange, dark cavern, at the Upper Ruins, Priest Ohm confronts Zoro, Gan Fall, and Wyper with his Ordeal of Iron. As the fight wears on, Shandian warriors, Nami, and Aisa make a sudden appearance.
translations.title: Concerto

translations.description: While Luffy remains lost in a strange, dark cavern, at the Upper Ruins, Priest Ohm confronts Zoro, Gan Fall, and Wyper with his Ordeal of Iron. As the fight wears on, Shandian warriors, Nami, and Aisa make a sudden appearance.
translations.title: 協奏曲(コンチェルト)

translations.description: After being swallowed by the giant snake, Nami, Gan Fall, and Aisa meet someone they never expected would be in the serpent's stomach. As Priest Ohm’s Ordeal of Iron comes to a close in the Upper Ruins, Zoro unleashes a powerful new technique.
translations.title: Pirate Zoro vs. Priest Ohm

translations.description: After being swallowed by the giant snake, Nami, Gan Fall, and Aisa meet someone they never expected would be in the serpent's stomach. As Priest Ohm’s Ordeal of Iron comes to a close in the Upper Ruins, Zoro unleashes a powerful new technique.
translations.title: 海賊ゾロ vs 神官オーム

translations.description: Arriving at Skypiea, the Straw Hats are instantly met with unfamiliar sights, objects, and customs. What's more, the god of the sky island deems the Blue Sea dwellers to be trespassing and casts his judgment upon them.
translations.title: Skypiea

translations.description: Llegando a Skypiea, los Sombrero de Paja inmediatamente se encuentran con vistas, objetos e incluso una aduana muy poco familiar. Lo que es más, el Dios de la Isla del Cielo considera que los visitantes del mar azul están haciendo un allanamiento y se desata un juicio sobre ellos.
translations.title: Skypiea

translations.description: En arrivant à Skypiea, les Chapeaux de Paille se frottent instantanément à des paysages, à des objets et à des coutumes totalement inconnus. De plus, le dieu de l'île céleste considère les habitants de la Mer Bleue comme des intrus et abat son jugement divin sur eux.
translations.title: Skypiea

translations.description: Arriving at Skypiea, the Straw Hats are instantly met with unfamiliar sights, objects, and customs. What's more, the god of the sky island deems the Blue Sea dwellers to be trespassing and casts his judgment upon them.
translations.title: スカイピア

translations.description: As they continue to traverse the Grand Line, the Straw Hats pass a ship with no sails, no Jolly Roger, and no captain. After an encounter with giant sea monkeys, they come upon an island where everything is much longer than usual.
translations.title: Adventure on a Long Island

translations.description: As they continue to traverse the Grand Line, the Straw Hats pass a ship with no sails, no Jolly Roger, and no captain. After an encounter with giant sea monkeys, they come upon an island where everything is much longer than usual.
translations.title: 長い島の冒険

translations.description: Luffy accepts Foxy’s challenge to a Davy Back Fight, a pirate contest in which the stakes are the crews themselves! Round #1 is the Donut Race, where each team races around the island in tiny boats made from just the scraps of three barrels.
translations.title: Donut Race!!

translations.title: No One Can Stop This Now

translations.description: After forming an unlikely alliance, Luffy rushes through Impel Down aided by Buggy's powers. Meanwhile, Ace finds himself with an unlikely companion as well when he exchanges words with a powerful pirate prisoner.

translations.title: 海侠のジンベエ

translations.description: Luffy and his deranged team pummel everything from Level 3 to Level 4 that dares to stand in their path. However, the powerful guard Minotaurus is ready to do some pummeling of his own while a boiling bath of blood awaits below.

translations.title: LV4 焦熱地獄

translations.description: With nowhere to run, Luffy's desperation to save Ace forces him to make a very grim sacrifice against his venomous adversary. Down in the frozen depths of Level 5, Bon Kurei rushes to his friend's aid, betting on a distant hope.

translations.title: ダチ

translations.description: Bon Kurei wanders through Level 5 in search of a mysterious missing prisoner. However, the fearsome wolves and bitter cold eventually take their toll, and he collapses in the Freezing Hell, all while Luffy's life continues to dwindle away.

translations.description: Luffy is back in action, and he prepares to set off, now with even more powerful allies who have ties to his old man. When they reach the lowest level of Impel Down, the legendary Level 6, they are in for a few new surprises.
translations.title: Infinite Hell

translations.description: A veritable all-star team on his side, Luffy and co. battle their way back up to Level 4. On Level 2, a massive riot erupts, plunging the prison into chaos. To further complicate matters, another infamous pirate breaks into Impel Down.

translations.title: やがて語られるもう一つの事件

translations.description: It is utter chaos in Impel Down, and between the sudden appearance of Blackbeard, the vice warden’s interference, and Magellan’s dogged attempts to restore order, the escape team just might see daylight yet!
translations.title: To Sunshine and Freedom

translations.description: It is utter chaos in Impel Down, and between the sudden appearance of Blackbeard, the vice warden’s interference, and Magellan’s dogged attempts to restore order, the escape team just might see daylight yet!
translations.title: 陽のあたるシャバへ

translations.description: Thanks to Jinbe’s quick thinking, Luffy and co. narrowly escape Impel Down. However, the Gates of Justice remain closed, and a horde of Navy ships is gaining on them. Then, just when all hope seems lost, a dear friend makes an all-or-nothing gamble.
translations.title: Thank You

translations.description: Thanks to Jinbe’s quick thinking, Luffy and co. narrowly escape Impel Down. However, the Gates of Justice remain closed, and a horde of Navy ships is gaining on them. Then, just when all hope seems lost, a dear friend makes an all-or-nothing gamble.
translations.title: ありがとう

translations.description: Luffy launches a daring rescue mission to break his big brother Ace from the government prison, Impel Down. It's a race to the prison's lowest levels — a literal journey through hell itself.
translations.title: Impel Down

translations.description: Luffy launches a daring rescue mission to break his big brother Ace from the government prison, Impel Down. It's a race to the prison's lowest levels — a literal journey through hell itself.
translations.title: インペルダウン

translations.description: Fifty warships, 100,000 marines, the Seven Warlords, and three admirals: Akainu, Aokiji, and Kizaru. The stage is set, and, as a battle with Whitebeard looms, Fleet Admiral Sengoku reveals a shocking truth about Ace.
translations.title: Navy Headquarters

translations.description: Cincuenta barcos de guerra, cien mil marinos, el Ouka Shichibukai, Tres Almirantes: Akainu, Aokiji y Kizaru. El escenario está listo, y mientras la batalla con Barbablanca se asoma, el Almirante de Flota Sengoku revela una impactante verdad sobre Ace.
translations.title: Cuartel General

translations.description: Fifty warships, 100,000 marines, the Seven Warlords, and three admirals: Akainu, Aokiji, and Kizaru. The stage is set, and, as a battle with Whitebeard looms, Fleet Admiral Sengoku reveals a shocking truth about Ace.
translations.title: 海軍本部

translations.description: To the surprise of the Navy, the Moby Dick surfaces in the middle of Marineford! On the deck stands Whitebeard, the man who Ace calls father, and his 14 commanders, the pirates he calls family, who share Luffy’s determination to stop the execution.
translations.title: Ace and Whitebeard

translations.description: Para sorpresa de la Marina, ¡el Moby Dick surge en la mitad de Marineford! En la cubierta se ve a Barbablanca, el hombre al cual Ace llama padre, y sus catorce comandantes, los piratas que él llama familia, quienes comparten la determinación de Luffy de detener la ejecución.
translations.title: Ace y Barbablanca

translations.description: To the surprise of the Navy, the Moby Dick surfaces in the middle of Marineford! On the deck stands Whitebeard, the man who Ace calls father, and his 14 commanders, the pirates he calls family, who share Luffy’s determination to stop the execution.
translations.title: エースと白ひげ

translations.description: The players have assembled at last! Whitebeard unleashes a tsunami that is set to swallow every marine and turn Navy HQ upside down. The fight has just begun, as Navy admirals and pirate commanders alike showcase their incredible abilities.
translations.title: Conflict at the Summit

translations.description: ¡Los participantes finalmente se han reunido! Barbablanca libera un maremoto que atenta a hundir a cada marino y dejar patas arriba al Cuartel de la Marina. La lucha recién comienza, pero los almirantes así como los comandantes despliegan sus increíbles habilidades.
translations.title: Conflicto en la cumbre

translations.description: The players have assembled at last! Whitebeard unleashes a tsunami that is set to swallow every marine and turn Navy HQ upside down. The fight has just begun, as Navy admirals and pirate commanders alike showcase their incredible abilities.
translations.title: 頂上決戦

translations.description: A larger-than-life ally risks his life to pave the way forward, and the Whitebeard Pirates rush toward Ace. However, just as their rescue mission picks up momentum, Sengoku employs a surprise tactic that turns the tide yet again.
translations.title: Justice Will Prevail!!

translations.description: Un enorme aliado ariesga su vida para abrir el camino, y los Piratas de Barbablanca corren hacia Ace. Sin embargo, cuando la misión de rescate está en su climax, Sengoku activa una táctica sorpresa que vuelve a emparejar las cosas.
translations.title: ¡¡La justicia prevalecerá!!

translations.description: A larger-than-life ally risks his life to pave the way forward, and the Whitebeard Pirates rush toward Ace. However, just as their rescue mission picks up momentum, Sengoku employs a surprise tactic that turns the tide yet again.
translations.title: 正義は勝つ!!

translations.description: Luffy leaps into the fray! Battling against familiar faces and new foes alike, he races toward the scaffold like a whirlwind of destruction, and, as his brother begs for him to turn back, Luffy shares some powerful words of his own.
translations.title: Luffy and Whitebeard

translations.description: ¡Luffy cae en la mitad del show! Luchando contra caras conocidas y nuevos enemigos, corre hacia la tarima, como un torbellino de destrucción, y, mientras su hermano le ruega que se devuelva, Luffy comparte algunas potentes palabras.
translations.title: Luffy y Barbablanca

translations.description: Luffy leaps into the fray! Battling against familiar faces and new foes alike, he races toward the scaffold like a whirlwind of destruction, and, as his brother begs for him to turn back, Luffy shares some powerful words of his own.
translations.title: ルフィと白ひげ

translations.description: Facing Kuma on the battlefield, Ivankov reveals their shared past, but his pleas to his old companion fall on deaf ears as Kuma continues his attacks. In a sea of confusion, only Doflamingo seems to know the truth.
translations.title: The Prisoners of Impel Down

translations.description: Enfrentándose a Kuma en el campo de batalla, Ivankov revela su pasado en común, pero sus plegarias a su antiguo compañero van a oidos sordos ya que Kuma sigue su ataque. En un mar de enredos, solo Doflamingo parece saber la verdad.
translations.title: Los prisioneros de Impel Down

translations.description: Facing Kuma on the battlefield, Ivankov reveals their shared past, but his pleas to his old companion fall on deaf ears as Kuma continues his attacks. In a sea of confusion, only Doflamingo seems to know the truth.
translations.title: インペルダウンの囚人達

translations.description: Luffy’s progress is halted by Mihawk, but the Whitebeard Pirates counter with a swordsman of their own. Then, when an army of human weapons encircle the battlefield, Luffy and his allies find themselves overwhelmed by their explosive attacks.
translations.title: The Whirl Spider

translations.description: El progreso de Luffy es interrumpido por Mihawk, pero los Piratas de Barbablanca contraatacan con su propio espadachín. Luego, cuando una armada de armas humanas rodea el campo de batalla, Luffy y sus aliados se encuentran sobrepasados por su explosivo ataque.
translations.title: El Remolino Araña

translations.description: Luffy’s progress is halted by Mihawk, but the Whitebeard Pirates counter with a swordsman of their own. Then, when an army of human weapons encircle the battlefield, Luffy and his allies find themselves overwhelmed by their explosive attacks.
translations.title: 海賊大渦蜘蛛スクアード

translations.description: Squard’s betrayal of Whitebeard sends ripples of distrust and uncertainty throughout the pirate alliance. And yet, Whitebeard’s faith will not be shattered, and it soon becomes clear that his allies are falling into a clever setup launched by the Navy.
translations.title: The Man Who Shook the World

translations.description: La traición de Squard hacia Barbablanca genera divisiones y confusión a través de toda la alianza pirata. Y aún así, la fe de Barbablanca no puede ser derribada, y pronto queda claro que todo fue una artimaña provocada por la Marina.
translations.title: El hombre que estremeció el mundo

translations.description: Squard’s betrayal of Whitebeard sends ripples of distrust and uncertainty throughout the pirate alliance. And yet, Whitebeard’s faith will not be shattered, and it soon becomes clear that his allies are falling into a clever setup launched by the Navy.
translations.title: 世界を揺らす男

translations.description: The pirates are trapped in the bay, held there by Akainu’s magma. Amid the chaos, the order for Ace’s execution is given, and Luffy makes a drastic decision that puts him face-to-face with the Navy’s most powerful men.
translations.title: Assault

translations.description: Los piratas están atrapados en la bahía gracias al magma de Akainu. En medio del caos, la orden de ejecutar a Ace es solicitada, por lo que Luffy toma la drástica decisión de ponerse cara a cara con los hombres más poderosos de la Marina.
translations.title: Asalto

translations.description: The pirates are trapped in the bay, held there by Akainu’s magma. Amid the chaos, the order for Ace’s execution is given, and Luffy makes a drastic decision that puts him face-to-face with the Navy’s most powerful men.
translations.title: 猛攻

translations.description: His adopted son within reach, Whitebeard charges forth, undeterred by the strongest the Navy has to offer. With both sides swinging between victory and defeat, the battlefield plunges into chaos. Then Marco takes to the sky and soars to Ace’s side!
translations.title: Oris Plaza

translations.description: Con su hijo adoptivo al alcance, Barbablanca va con todo, sin inmutarse por lo más fuerte que la Marina puede ofrecerle. Con ambos lados tambaleándose entre la victoria y la derrota, el campo de batalla se envuelve en caos. Entonces, ¡Marco llega desde el cielo a tratar de llegar al lado de Ace!
translations.title: Plaza Oris

translations.description: His adopted son within reach, Whitebeard charges forth, undeterred by the strongest the Navy has to offer. With both sides swinging between victory and defeat, the battlefield plunges into chaos. Then Marco takes to the sky and soars to Ace’s side!
translations.title: マリンフォード海軍本部オリス広場

translations.description: Faced with the might of the admirals, even Whitebeard's commanders falter. Refusing to relent, Luffy begs Ivankov for a final chance at victory. Amid a bevy of marines, an old friend of Luffy’s appears for a much too premature reunion.
translations.title: The White Monster

translations.description: Frente a los poderosos almirantes, incluso los comandantes de Barbablanca tambalean. Negándose a ceder, Luffy le ruega a Ivankov por una última oportunidad para ganar. En medio de un grupo de marinos, un viejo amigo de Luffy aparece para una reunión muy prematura.
translations.title: Monstruo Blanco

translations.description: Faced with the might of the admirals, even Whitebeard's commanders falter. Refusing to relent, Luffy begs Ivankov for a final chance at victory. Amid a bevy of marines, an old friend of Luffy’s appears for a much too premature reunion.
translations.title: 白い怪物

translations.description: Having borne witness to Luffy’s latent powers, the Navy sends everything they have at him. But thanks to Ivankov’s quick thinking, Luffy ascends toward Ace. Garp, unable to watch any longer, leaps into Luffy’s path.
translations.title: The Execution Platform

translations.description: Habiendo presenciado el poder latente de Luffy, la Marina va con todo hacia él. Pero gracias al pensamiento rápido de Ivankov, Luffy logra llegar con Ace. Garp ya no pudiendo seguir solo como espectador, se interpone en el camino de Luffy.
translations.title: La Plataforma de Ejecución

translations.description: Having borne witness to Luffy’s latent powers, the Navy sends everything they have at him. But thanks to Ivankov’s quick thinking, Luffy ascends toward Ace. Garp, unable to watch any longer, leaps into Luffy’s path.
translations.title: 処刑台

translations.description: Ace is free at last, and the pair of brothers are unstoppable! Although the Whitebeard Pirates are emboldened by their teamwork, their captain is not convinced that their escape will come so easily, and Whitebeard makes a difficult decision.
translations.title: The Times They Are A-Changin'

translations.description: ¡Ace es finalmente libre, y el par de hermanos son imparables! Pese a que los Piratas de Barbablanca están envalentonados por su trabajo en equipo, su capitán no está convencido de la facilidad con la que podrán huir, por lo que Barbablanca toma una difícil decisión.
translations.title: Los tiempos están cambiando

translations.description: Ace is free at last, and the pair of brothers are unstoppable! Although the Whitebeard Pirates are emboldened by their teamwork, their captain is not convinced that their escape will come so easily, and Whitebeard makes a difficult decision.
translations.title: The Times They Are A-Changin' -時代は変わる-

translations.description: Ace protects his brother from Akainu but suffers a mortal blow in the process. Jinbe and the Whitebeard Pirates rush to his aid but soon realize he is far beyond help. As Ace takes his final breaths, he imparts a heartfelt message.
translations.title: Thank You for Loving Me

translations.description: Ace protege a su hermano de Akainu, pero sufre un ataque mortal en el proceso. Jinbe y los Piratas de Barbablanca se apuran a dar socorro, pero pronto se dan cuenta que nada pueden hacer. Mientras Ace da sus últimos respiros, imparte un sentido mensaje.
translations.title: Gracias de todo corazón por quererme

translations.description: Ace protects his brother from Akainu but suffers a mortal blow in the process. Jinbe and the Whitebeard Pirates rush to his aid but soon realize he is far beyond help. As Ace takes his final breaths, he imparts a heartfelt message.
translations.title: ポートガス・D・エース死す (probably a custom title, will have to check the episode for this one)

translations.description: Blackbeard appears, Thatch’s murder and Ace’s capture all part of a terrifying plan that no one could have imagined! With the war in its final stage, Whitebeard fights to avenge his fallen sons and to punish the traitor who plotted his undoing.
translations.title: Edward Newgate

translations.description: Barbanegra aparece, ¡la muerte de Thatch y la captura de Ace eran parte de un temible plan que nadie se podría haber imaginado! Con la guerra en su etapa final, Barbablanca pelea para vengar a sus hijos caídos y castigar al traidor que provocó todo esto.
translations.title: Edward Newgate

translations.description: Blackbeard appears, Thatch’s murder and Ace’s capture all part of a terrifying plan that no one could have imagined! With the war in its final stage, Whitebeard fights to avenge his fallen sons and to punish the traitor who plotted his undoing.
translations.title: 大海賊エドワード・二ューゲート

translations.description: Though Ace and Whitebeard have been killed, the Navy seeks to wipe out every last pirate, even as they retreat. In the confusion, Akainu sets his eyes on the unconscious Luffy. Meanwhile, Blackbeard reveals his true scheme and a terrifying new power!
translations.title: A Gift to a New Era

translations.description: Pese a que Ace y Barbablanca han sido asesinados, la Marina busca deshacerse de cada pirata posible, aunque estén en retirada. En la confusión, Akainu se fija en un Luffy inconsciente. Mientras, Barbanegra revela su verdadero plan, ¡y un temible nuevo poder!
translations.title: Un regalo para la nueva era

translations.description: Though Ace and Whitebeard have been killed, the Navy seeks to wipe out every last pirate, even as they retreat. In the confusion, Akainu sets his eyes on the unconscious Luffy. Meanwhile, Blackbeard reveals his true scheme and a terrifying new power!
translations.title: 新時代へ贈るもの

translations.description: Senseless violence dyes the battlefield red with blood. Luffy’s allies struggle to save him as the admirals maintain their assault. Suddenly, the Red Hair Pirates appear! Narrowly missing a reunion with Luffy, Shanks utters a speech on the battlefield.
translations.title: The War's Conclusion

translations.description: Violencia sin sentido tiñe el campo de batalla de color rojo con sangre. Los aliados de Luffy luchan por salvarlo mientras los almirantes se mantienen en la lucha. De la nada, ¡los piratas del Pelirrojo aparecen! Casi reuniéndose con Luffy, Shanks da un gran discurso en el campo de batalla.
translations.title: El fin de la guerra

translations.description: Senseless violence dyes the battlefield red with blood. Luffy’s allies struggle to save him as the admirals maintain their assault. Suddenly, the Red Hair Pirates appear! Narrowly missing a reunion with Luffy, Shanks utters a speech on the battlefield.
translations.title: 終戦

translations.description: Pirate Whitebeard and his allies on one side; the Navy and its Seven Warlords on the other. At the center of it all: Portgas D. Ace and his unspeakable past and heritage. Luffy races to Ace's execution scaffold as a battle between the world's most powerful people unfolds.
translations.title: Marineford

translations.description: El pirata Barbablanca y sus aliados por un lado; la Marina y los Shichibukai del otro. Y en el centro de todo, Portgas D. Ace y su pasado oculto y herencia. Luffy corre hacia la tarima de ejecución de Ace en una batalla entre las personas más poderosas del mundo.
translations.title: Marineford

translations.description: Pirate Whitebeard and his allies on one side; the Navy and its Seven Warlords on the other. At the center of it all: Portgas D. Ace and his unspeakable past and heritage. Luffy races to Ace's execution scaffold as a battle between the world's most powerful people unfolds.
translations.title: マリンフォード

translations.description: The Summit War has thrown the entire world into chaos. Emboldened by Whitebeard's final words, pirates once again envision a wave they can ride into a new era. At Hancock’s order, Luffy is taken to Amazon Lily to hide from the Navy while he recovers.
translations.title: Creeping Future
